WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

2
00:01:46.940 --> 00:01:48.775
<i>My dear children.</i>

3
00:01:49.401 --> 00:01:53.614
<i>It is now better than several years
since I moved to New York</i>

4
00:01:54.406 --> 00:01:57.534
<i>and I haven't seen you
as much as I would like to.</i>

5
00:01:58.660 --> 00:02:02.414
<i>I hope you will come to this
ceremony of Papal honours.</i>

6
00:02:02.539 --> 00:02:04.833
<i>given for my charitable work.</i>

7
00:02:07.044 --> 00:02:10.005
<i>The only wealth
in this world is children.</i>

8
00:02:10.130 --> 00:02:12.883
<i>More than all the money
and power on earth.</i>

9
00:02:14.134 --> 00:02:16.303
<i>you are my treasure.</i>

10
00:02:17.846 --> 00:02:20.015
<i>Anthony and Mary.</i>

11
00:02:20.140 --> 00:02:24.853
<i>although I entrusted your education to
your mother for your own best interest.</i>

12
00:02:24.978 --> 00:02:29.775
<i>I look forward to seeing you. and to
a new period of harmony in our lives.</i>

13
00:02:31.860 --> 00:02:36.198
<i>Perhaps you might prevail upon your
mother to come to this celebration.</i>

14
00:02:36.823 --> 00:02:41.370
<i>and that from time to time. we can all
see each other at family functions.</i>

15
00:02:42.788 --> 00:02:46.917
<i>Anyway. I remain your loving father.</i>

16
00:03:15.612 --> 00:03:18.115
Hail Mary. full of grace...

17
00:03:21.577 --> 00:03:23.996
...blessed art Thou amongst women...

18
00:03:24.746 --> 00:03:27.749
...and blessed is the fruit
of Thy womb. Jesus.

19
00:03:29.001 --> 00:03:33.172
Holy Mary. mother of God.
pray for us sinners...

20
00:03:57.154 --> 00:04:02.951
Almighty God. bless the insignia
of Saint Sebastian the martyr.

21
00:04:03.076 --> 00:04:08.582
that it may contribute to the sacredness
of him to whom it is given.

22
00:04:20.719 --> 00:04:24.056
Do you. Michael. promise to be faithful

23
00:04:24.181 --> 00:04:26.642
to the noble purposes of this Order.

24
00:04:27.351 --> 00:04:32.022
to have a special care for the poor.
the needy and those who are ill?

25
00:04:32.147 --> 00:04:33.899
I do so promise.

26
00:04:48.747 --> 00:04:51.542
May the blessing of Almighty God.

27
00:04:51.667 --> 00:04:56.505
Father. Son and Holy Spirit

28
00:04:56.630 --> 00:05:01.385
descend upon you
and remain with you forever.

29
00:06:31.642 --> 00:06:34.186
Vincent. our name is not on the list.

30
00:06:36.730 --> 00:06:40.567
Write it in. Mancini. M-A-N-C-I-N-I.

31
00:06:42.236 --> 00:06:44.488
- Problem?
- My name isn't on the list.

32
00:06:44.613 --> 00:06:49.159
- Then you have to leave immediately.
- You want to dance with me?

33
00:06:49.284 --> 00:06:52.329
Joe. it's Vinnie. These are our guests.

34
00:06:52.454 --> 00:06:54.331
I'm sorry. I'm sorry. sir.

35
00:06:54.498 --> 00:06:56.583
Welcome to the party.

36
00:07:47.509 --> 00:07:51.638
- It's good to see you.
- Good to see you. This is my husband.

37
00:07:51.763 --> 00:07:53.849
- Sit down.
- My son. Anthony.

38
00:07:55.100 --> 00:08:00.022
The Order of Saint Sebastian is one of
the highest honours the Church awards.

39
00:08:00.147 --> 00:08:02.357
It was first granted by Pope...

40
00:08:02.482 --> 00:08:05.611
What about Mr Corleone's connections
with gambling?

41
00:08:06.153 --> 00:08:07.738
The press kits have...

42
00:08:07.821 --> 00:08:09.990
What about his involvement
with the underworld?

43
00:08:10.115 --> 00:08:11.200
Cut the crap.

44
00:08:12.201 --> 00:08:14.786
The Pope. the Holy Father himself.

45
00:08:14.912 --> 00:08:19.374
has today blessed Michael Corleone.
Do you know better than the Pope?

46
00:08:20.167 --> 00:08:23.212
Vincent! She loves you.

47
00:08:23.337 --> 00:08:24.880
Yeah?

48
00:08:28.800 --> 00:08:30.302
I love you too.

49
00:08:36.016 --> 00:08:38.810
Hi. Vincent. I remember you.

50
00:08:40.562 --> 00:08:44.399
- From where?
- The last party we were at together.

51
00:08:44.525 --> 00:08:47.486
- Did you come to the club?
- No. it was a wedding.

52
00:08:49.863 --> 00:08:52.199
I was eight and you were 15.

53
00:08:53.367 --> 00:08:56.203
I had many girlfriends when I was 15.

54
00:08:56.328 --> 00:08:58.288
- Eight-year-olds?
- Especially them.

55
00:09:00.707 --> 00:09:02.668
Where's Mary?

56
00:09:02.793 --> 00:09:07.506
Would somebody please hail Mary?
Excuse me. Your Excellency.

57
00:09:07.631 --> 00:09:11.385
You haven't kissed me hello yet.
Relatives always kiss.

58
00:09:12.094 --> 00:09:14.972
- Now we're related?
- I'm your little cousin.

59
00:09:22.604 --> 00:09:25.482
- Who's your father?
- I'll give you a hint.

60
00:09:26.775 --> 00:09:28.360
He's Italian.

61
00:09:28.485 --> 00:09:31.613
Mary. we've been waiting for you.

62
00:09:31.780 --> 00:09:35.826
Remember to keep your voice low.

63
00:09:35.951 --> 00:09:38.287
And smile. Don't forget to smile.

64
00:09:57.806 --> 00:10:01.852
The honourary chairman of
the Vito Corleone Foundation.

65
00:10:01.977 --> 00:10:04.021
my daughter. Mary Corleone.

66
00:10:13.572 --> 00:10:14.781
Thanks.

67
00:10:16.325 --> 00:10:20.829
I think I inherited my father's love
for speechmaking. Here it goes.

68
00:10:22.539 --> 00:10:26.919
The Vito Corleone Foundation helps
the poor in every country.

69
00:10:27.044 --> 00:10:30.923
gives grants to artists.
funds medical research.

70
00:10:31.048 --> 00:10:35.594
and is particularly dedicated
to the resurrection of Sicily.

71
00:10:36.303 --> 00:10:38.347
Archbishop Gilday.

72
00:10:38.472 --> 00:10:44.520
here is 100 million dollars for the poor
of Sicily. in the name of Vito Corleone.

73
00:10:45.145 --> 00:10:47.397
Don't spend it all in one place.

74
00:11:04.623 --> 00:11:09.586
Mary. I'm so proud of you.

75
00:11:16.385 --> 00:11:18.011
Michael...

76
00:11:18.136 --> 00:11:20.806
You've done a wonderful thing for Sicily.

77
00:11:21.682 --> 00:11:25.143
Let's hope that the money gets
to the people who need it.

78
00:11:25.269 --> 00:11:26.436
Amen.

79
00:11:26.562 --> 00:11:31.441
...the most important part:
Johnny Fontane!

80
00:11:39.908 --> 00:11:42.744
Thank you very much.
I'm happy to be here.

81
00:11:42.870 --> 00:11:48.250
I would like you to join me in honouring
Commendatore Michael Corleone.

82
00:11:52.421 --> 00:11:55.549
I have something special
for our godfather.

83
00:11:55.674 --> 00:12:00.053
I happen to know his favourite song.
Michael. where are you going?

84
00:12:00.179 --> 00:12:03.640
I'm off to the kitchen
to hear some Tony Bennett records.

85
00:12:04.933 --> 00:12:07.311
Your favourite song. "Salsiccia's Own".

86
00:12:07.436 --> 00:12:10.355
I'm having a salsiccia sandwich.
I'll be back.

87
00:12:43.514 --> 00:12:44.890
Hello. Kay.

88
00:12:54.900 --> 00:12:57.653
Congratulations. Michael.
That's quite an honour.

89
00:12:57.778 --> 00:13:00.572
But a little expensive. wouldn't you say?

90
00:13:03.408 --> 00:13:06.203
- Cake?
- No. thank you.

91
00:13:19.591 --> 00:13:22.719
- It's been a long time. hasn't it?
- Yeah.

92
00:13:22.845 --> 00:13:24.638
- Eight years.
- Yeah.

93
00:13:25.472 --> 00:13:27.140
You look wonderful.

94
00:13:30.686 --> 00:13:35.065
Your son has something he wants to
talk to you about. I came here for him.

95
00:14:08.515 --> 00:14:13.645
- What's wrong with being a lawyer?
- He wants his life to be in music.

96
00:14:15.480 --> 00:14:19.610
Music is great. I love music.
But he should finish what he started.

97
00:14:19.735 --> 00:14:20.986
Anthony...

98
00:14:21.653 --> 00:14:23.906
- I'm going my own way.
- Your own way?

99
00:14:24.907 --> 00:14:26.658
- Professional singer?
- Yes.

100
00:14:26.742 --> 00:14:29.745
What happens if you fail?

101
00:14:29.870 --> 00:14:32.873
- I won't fail.
- Men always believe that.

102
00:14:32.998 --> 00:14:37.002
A law degree is like taking
out insurance.

103
00:14:37.836 --> 00:14:41.507
- After that you can work for me...
- I will never work for you.

104
00:14:42.799 --> 00:14:44.510
I have bad memories.

105
00:14:46.261 --> 00:14:48.597
Every family has bad memories.

106
00:14:52.226 --> 00:14:56.563
I'll always be your son. but won't have
anything to do with your business.

107
00:14:59.066 --> 00:15:02.319
Anthony... finish the law degree.

108
00:15:03.862 --> 00:15:04.905
No.

109
00:15:21.755 --> 00:15:25.425
Well. that he got from you. That "no".

110
00:15:28.387 --> 00:15:33.225
- You could've helped me convince him.
- Convince him of what?

111
00:15:33.934 --> 00:15:35.102
Of what?

112
00:15:35.978 --> 00:15:40.357
He throws his life away.
He throws greatness away.

113
00:15:41.483 --> 00:15:43.068
This is greatness?

114
00:15:44.570 --> 00:15:48.824
Now that you're so respectable.
you're more dangerous than ever.

115
00:15:48.949 --> 00:15:52.828
I preferred you when you were
just a common Mafia hood.

116
00:15:53.996 --> 00:15:55.164
Okay.

117
00:15:56.456 --> 00:15:59.668
- Can we talk common sense here?
- All right.

118
00:16:06.175 --> 00:16:08.510
Tony knows that you killed Fredo.

119
00:16:15.017 --> 00:16:18.228
- What did you come here for?
- To protect my son.

120
00:16:18.353 --> 00:16:22.983
Not to see you disguised by your
church. That was a shameful ceremony.

121
00:16:27.613 --> 00:16:29.948
I spent my life protecting my son.

122
00:16:30.574 --> 00:16:33.911
I spent my life protecting my family!

123
00:16:34.036 --> 00:16:35.996
Let's be reasonable. okay?

124
00:16:37.206 --> 00:16:41.335
That's your big thing. isn't it. Michael?
Reason.

125
00:16:42.419 --> 00:16:45.672
- backed up by murder.
- Oh. God.

126
00:16:47.424 --> 00:16:50.719
- You hate me. You hate me.
- No.

127
00:16:50.844 --> 00:16:52.513
I don't hate you.

128
00:16:54.306 --> 00:16:55.807
I dread you.

129
00:16:59.603 --> 00:17:05.484
I did what I could. Kay. to protect all
of you from the horrors of this world.

130
00:17:06.860 --> 00:17:08.862
But you became my horror.

131
00:17:18.247 --> 00:17:21.500
The children still love you. though.
Especially Mary.

132
00:17:24.545 --> 00:17:26.171
That's something.

133
00:17:28.507 --> 00:17:31.844
We can build on that. For their sake.

134
00:17:35.722 --> 00:17:36.974
let's try.

135
00:17:37.641 --> 00:17:42.771
Only if you let Tony go free to have
his own life. away from you.

136
00:17:49.820 --> 00:17:51.446
I'll let Tony go.

137
00:17:53.949 --> 00:17:55.367
Thank you.

138
00:18:28.734 --> 00:18:30.611
- Hi.
- Hi.

139
00:18:32.571 --> 00:18:37.576
You could hurt somebody with those.
Let me show you around.

140
00:18:37.701 --> 00:18:39.953
Can you get me an interview
with Corleone?

141
00:18:40.078 --> 00:18:44.082
No. I'm a relative. but I can't do that.
What else can I do for you?

142
00:18:45.542 --> 00:18:48.295
- Handsome. but useless.
- Oh. yeah?

143
00:18:48.420 --> 00:18:51.131
- That's okay. I'll gamble.
- Do you like to gamble?

144
00:18:51.256 --> 00:18:54.927
Let's go to Atlantic City.
I'll show you how to gamble.

145
00:18:55.052 --> 00:18:59.556
- How do I know what numbers to bet?
- Do I look like a guy who's gonna lose?

146
00:18:59.681 --> 00:19:00.849
Well...

147
00:19:03.435 --> 00:19:05.312
Spooky-looking guy there.

148
00:19:05.437 --> 00:19:10.734
- What's a guy like that doing here?
- That's Joey Zasa's bulldog.

149
00:19:10.859 --> 00:19:12.736
- You know him?
- Yeah. I do.

150
00:19:13.737 --> 00:19:17.908
His name is Anthony Squigilaro.
They call him "The Ant".

151
00:19:18.659 --> 00:19:20.911
He dips his bullets in cyanide.

152
00:19:29.461 --> 00:19:30.963
Don Altobello.

153
00:19:32.422 --> 00:19:35.676
<i>- I've come to pay my respects.
- Grazie.</i>

154
00:19:39.137 --> 00:19:41.431
You honour my father's friendship.

155
00:19:41.557 --> 00:19:43.475
Where is my goddaughter?

156
00:19:45.352 --> 00:19:47.396
- Constanza!
- Don Altobello.

157
00:19:47.980 --> 00:19:52.234
It was not so long ago
that I held you in these old hands.

158
00:20:00.450 --> 00:20:05.372
Michael. I've lost all the venom.
all the juice of youth.

159
00:20:05.497 --> 00:20:10.377
I've lost the lust for women.
and now my mind is clear.

160
00:20:11.086 --> 00:20:17.176
My duty to God is clear.
I have a special favour to ask of you.

161
00:20:18.760 --> 00:20:25.309
Can I attach my name
to the Vito Corleone Foundation.

162
00:20:25.976 --> 00:20:30.814
so that you and I can be joined
in name and spirit?

163
00:20:33.317 --> 00:20:37.946
- One million dollars.
- A lot of money...

164
00:20:40.657 --> 00:20:44.411
- Godfather.
- Don Altobello. you have such a heart.

165
00:20:47.289 --> 00:20:51.418
<i>Come. let's go and sample
some of that old vino.</i>

166
00:20:58.008 --> 00:21:01.261
The Vatican knows nothing
about these shareholders.

167
00:21:01.386 --> 00:21:02.513
Good.

168
00:21:02.638 --> 00:21:07.267
I have a tendency to worry. We've
increased our position substantially.

169
00:21:07.392 --> 00:21:11.730
- Naturally. I worry.
- Stop worrying. we have an agreement.

170
00:21:12.731 --> 00:21:15.526
Good. How do you think
I got this grey hair?

171
00:21:15.651 --> 00:21:21.114
Two seconds... Thank you for your
contribution to the swimming-pool.

172
00:21:21.240 --> 00:21:25.244
We need your help on Sam Wallace's
candidacy for judgeship.

173
00:21:25.369 --> 00:21:27.830
- We can always use a good judge.
- Thanks.

174
00:21:27.955 --> 00:21:29.456
Andrew!

175
00:21:29.581 --> 00:21:33.293
My godson Andrew Hagen.
My brother Tom's eldest boy.

176
00:21:33.460 --> 00:21:37.756
He's been assistant to Bishop Breelan
for three years.

177
00:21:37.881 --> 00:21:41.969
- Hopes to be assigned to the Vatican.
- Rome needs fine young priests.

178
00:21:42.094 --> 00:21:44.972
His mother Teresa Hagen.
Bishop Gilday.

179
00:21:45.973 --> 00:21:47.349
Honoured to meet you.

180
00:21:47.474 --> 00:21:50.269
Mr Corleone. Hi. Grace Hamilton.

181
00:21:51.603 --> 00:21:55.858
Vincent Mancini promised to tell you
about me. That maybe you'd see me.

182
00:21:56.233 --> 00:21:59.194
- Did Vincent Mancini call about her?
- No.

183
00:21:59.319 --> 00:22:03.407
- You promised to stay out there. twice.
- I know.

184
00:22:04.575 --> 00:22:08.328
Joey Zasa showed up.
He's waiting in the lobby.

185
00:22:08.495 --> 00:22:12.624
<i>He wants to personally
congratulate you. Show his respect.</i>

186
00:22:12.749 --> 00:22:17.462
<i>- Do I have to see him?
- He says you're his patron.</i>

187
00:22:20.632 --> 00:22:22.593
Hey. Vinnie!

188
00:22:23.552 --> 00:22:26.054
- Who's your favourite aunt?
- You are.

189
00:22:28.724 --> 00:22:32.019
Today I'll talk to Michael
about your little problem.

190
00:22:32.853 --> 00:22:35.898
If you'd warned me. I would have
worn a better suit.

191
00:22:37.399 --> 00:22:40.110
The Meucci Association has elected you

192
00:22:40.235 --> 00:22:42.696
Italian-American Man of the Year.

193
00:22:44.573 --> 00:22:45.824
Meucci...

194
00:22:48.744 --> 00:22:50.162
Who's Meucci?

195
00:22:51.413 --> 00:22:57.127
The Italian-American who invented
the telephone. one year before Bell.

196
00:23:00.839 --> 00:23:03.634
And this is the reason
you've come today?

197
00:23:10.682 --> 00:23:11.725
I...

198
00:23:14.895 --> 00:23:17.147
I've got a stone in my shoe.

199
00:23:18.565 --> 00:23:20.817
A two-bit punk who works for me.

200
00:23:21.735 --> 00:23:24.863
The one who thinks he's related to you.

201
00:23:27.282 --> 00:23:28.492
A bastard.

202
00:23:32.412 --> 00:23:36.542
He's here. Vincent Mancini.
He's at the party.

203
00:23:39.837 --> 00:23:41.255
Bring him in.

204
00:23:42.631 --> 00:23:45.008
I think it's good that we talk.

205
00:23:45.843 --> 00:23:47.719
<i>No. grazie.</i>

206
00:23:49.680 --> 00:23:51.348
I have a problem...

207
00:23:51.974 --> 00:23:57.938
...and I want to find out if it is
my problem or your problem.

208
00:23:58.063 --> 00:24:02.860
Your business is your business. I have
no interests or percentages from it.

209
00:24:04.319 --> 00:24:07.281
Good. Then it's my problem.

210
00:24:11.493 --> 00:24:15.706
Michael. you know Vincent Mancini.
Sonny's boy.

211
00:24:17.666 --> 00:24:20.627
- How are you. Mr Corleone?
- How are you?

212
00:24:20.752 --> 00:24:24.381
- Good. How are you? Good party.
- You like it?

213
00:24:24.506 --> 00:24:27.551
- Yes. I had to sneak in.
- You're dressed for it.

214
00:24:32.181 --> 00:24:35.851
So. what's the trouble
between you and Mr Joe Zasa?

215
00:24:38.061 --> 00:24:42.149
- Just trouble. I'll take care of it.
- That's foolish of you.

216
00:24:42.274 --> 00:24:46.945
Foolish of me? It's a little foolish
of this guy. don't you think? Right?

217
00:24:48.697 --> 00:24:51.700
- Right?
- Temper like his father...

218
00:24:52.409 --> 00:24:53.619
Vincent...

219
00:24:55.621 --> 00:25:01.001
Mr Joe Zasa now owns what used to
be the Corleone business in New York.

220
00:25:01.126 --> 00:25:04.796
Out of kindness. he gave you
a job in his family.

221
00:25:04.922 --> 00:25:07.382
You took it against my advice.

222
00:25:07.508 --> 00:25:12.596
I offered you something better in the
legitimate world. You turned me down.

223
00:25:12.721 --> 00:25:17.392
Now you both come to me with this bad
blood. What do you expect me to do?

224
00:25:19.478 --> 00:25:20.896
- Am I a gangster?
- No...

225
00:25:20.979 --> 00:25:25.651
That was Papa's neighbourhood.
Zasa runs it like a disgrace!

226
00:25:25.776 --> 00:25:29.780
- That's the past. Connie.
- I earned that territory.

227
00:25:29.905 --> 00:25:33.408
The Commission gave it to me
and you approved.

228
00:25:33.534 --> 00:25:34.493
Yes.

229
00:25:34.618 --> 00:25:39.122
I came for the party. not to ask for help.
I could kill this bastard.

230
00:25:39.248 --> 00:25:40.582
So kill him.

231
00:25:42.125 --> 00:25:45.045
What does all this have to do with me?

232
00:25:45.170 --> 00:25:50.092
Well. he goes behind your back.
saying "Fuck Michael Corleone".

233
00:25:50.259 --> 00:25:52.803
Say it to his face. one time!

234
00:25:54.221 --> 00:25:59.184
Mr Corleone. all bastards are liars.
Shakespeare wrote poems about it.

235
00:25:59.309 --> 00:26:02.145
What am I going to do with this guy?

236
00:26:08.193 --> 00:26:12.656
Joey. if there's some guy
running around this city.

237
00:26:12.781 --> 00:26:15.284
saying. "Fuck Michael Corleone"...

238
00:26:16.702 --> 00:26:19.746
...what do we do
with a piece of shit like that?

239
00:26:22.040 --> 00:26:23.959
He's a fucking dog.

240
00:26:30.799 --> 00:26:34.219
Yes. it's true.
If anyone would say such a thing.

241
00:26:34.344 --> 00:26:37.556
they would not be a friend.
they would be a dog.

242
00:26:43.604 --> 00:26:49.484
- My interests don't conflict with his.
- You don't know how much they do.

243
00:26:49.610 --> 00:26:50.944
Quiet. Vincent.

244
00:26:51.069 --> 00:26:53.155
He needs your support!

245
00:26:53.280 --> 00:26:55.866
Don't let me work for this guy.
let me work for you.

246
00:26:55.991 --> 00:27:01.705
As what? Tough guy? I don't need
tough guys. I need more lawyers.

247
00:27:04.917 --> 00:27:10.756
Since we have no conflicts or debts.
I accept your tribute. I wish you well.

248
00:27:12.508 --> 00:27:16.762
Vincent. make your peace
with Mr Joe Zasa. Go on.

249
00:27:27.397 --> 00:27:28.690
<i>Bastardo...</i>

250
00:27:34.321 --> 00:27:36.990
Vinnie. what's the matter with you?

251
00:27:37.115 --> 00:27:38.909
Get him out of here.

252
00:27:40.828 --> 00:27:42.496
Jesus Christ...

253
00:27:43.580 --> 00:27:45.415
- I told Connie this wasn't the right time.
- Close it.

254
00:27:45.541 --> 00:27:50.587
I know you're into Wall Street.
but you're still the final word.

255
00:27:50.712 --> 00:27:53.465
I want to protect you from these guys.
Your lawyers can't.

256
00:27:53.590 --> 00:27:56.051
- But you can?
- Yeah. I can do that.

257
00:27:57.678 --> 00:27:59.513
Why should I be afraid of Zasa?

258
00:27:59.638 --> 00:28:02.808
You stop him from rising
in the Commission.

259
00:28:02.933 --> 00:28:06.103
I say we make him dead.
Give me the order. I'll do it.

260
00:28:06.228 --> 00:28:07.688
- You'll do it?
- Yeah.

261
00:28:12.234 --> 00:28:16.738
Maybe you should come with me
for a few weeks. See what happens.

262
00:28:17.447 --> 00:28:19.408
- Okay.
- See if you learn.

263
00:28:20.868 --> 00:28:23.328
And we'll talk about your future.

264
00:28:24.872 --> 00:28:26.623
I won't let you down.

265
00:28:33.255 --> 00:28:34.798
It's about ready.

266
00:28:40.721 --> 00:28:41.805
So. what happened?

267
00:28:41.930 --> 00:28:43.056
What happened?

268
00:28:43.182 --> 00:28:46.310
If I'm in a room with Zasa.
what happens? I bit his ear off.

269
00:28:46.435 --> 00:28:48.562
Here we go. Watch the card.

270
00:28:51.273 --> 00:28:52.608
Hold it!

271
00:28:54.818 --> 00:28:56.486
- Vincent...
- Yeah.

272
00:28:56.612 --> 00:28:58.697
Take the picture with us.

273
00:29:05.746 --> 00:29:07.122
Nice jacket.

274
00:29:09.166 --> 00:29:11.543
Closer to the centre. sir.

275
00:29:13.378 --> 00:29:15.255
Smile!

276
00:29:34.858 --> 00:29:39.196
Godfather. this is the cake for you
and your family from Enzo the baker.

277
00:29:40.489 --> 00:29:42.282
Do you want to do it?

278
00:30:26.577 --> 00:30:29.580
Cent'anni! Cent'anni!

279
00:31:26.678 --> 00:31:29.515
- Vincent?
- What do you want. sweetheart?

280
00:31:31.808 --> 00:31:33.352
Do you love me?

281
00:31:34.811 --> 00:31:37.231
- Come on. go to bed.
- Come on. say it.

282
00:31:39.107 --> 00:31:40.817
I love you.

283
00:31:41.527 --> 00:31:43.362
I love you. too.

284
00:31:45.823 --> 00:31:47.407
You've got a cat?

285
00:31:53.997 --> 00:31:56.708
Go get us some water. I'm thirsty.
Come on.

286
00:31:57.668 --> 00:31:59.086
Come on.

287
00:32:06.260 --> 00:32:08.846
Well. I guess I know my place.

288
00:32:09.721 --> 00:32:12.391
I can't believe I'm actually doing this.

289
00:32:13.183 --> 00:32:16.728
"Get me water. bake me a cake"...
What happened to "please"?

290
00:33:02.357 --> 00:33:05.027
Good boy. Sackface. Go for a walk.

291
00:33:14.119 --> 00:33:16.830
- Let her go.
- Cut her throat. man.

292
00:33:19.500 --> 00:33:22.294
- What did you say?
- Cut her fucking throat.

293
00:33:25.464 --> 00:33:28.383
- Okay. chief...
- Drop your gun or he'll cut her throat.

294
00:33:28.509 --> 00:33:32.554
I hardly know her. so cut her.
What the fuck do I care?

295
00:33:34.473 --> 00:33:37.935
You've got no choice. She'll be dead.

296
00:33:38.060 --> 00:33:41.855
If you do. I'll kill you both.
Give up that knife. I'll let you go.

297
00:33:41.980 --> 00:33:44.399
Cut her throat! Right now!

298
00:33:44.525 --> 00:33:50.447
I'll do something that'll convince you.
Don't get frightened. Just watch me.

299
00:33:55.118 --> 00:33:56.578
Oh. shit!

300
00:33:58.622 --> 00:34:00.999
Drop the knife. Drop it!

301
00:34:01.124 --> 00:34:07.548
Good boy. Sit down. I want to talk
to you. It was a wise choice. Sit down.

302
00:34:07.673 --> 00:34:09.132
Lose the mask.

303
00:34:12.386 --> 00:34:14.638
Relax. have a smoke. You smoke?

304
00:34:17.307 --> 00:34:19.726
Whose idea was this? Who sent you?

305
00:34:20.477 --> 00:34:23.230
Tell me who sent you.

306
00:34:25.357 --> 00:34:27.985
- No one.
- Did you take a look at this guy?

307
00:34:28.110 --> 00:34:30.070
- Yeah.
- Who sent you?

308
00:34:32.614 --> 00:34:34.908
It was Joey Zasa.

309
00:34:49.089 --> 00:34:50.591
Are you okay?

310
00:34:53.719 --> 00:34:56.722
- You were going to let them kill me!
- No. I wasn't...

311
00:34:56.847 --> 00:34:59.224
You pig! You sick fuck!

312
00:35:01.351 --> 00:35:04.813
You wanted gambling. That's gambling.
Call the police.

313
00:35:09.568 --> 00:35:12.738
- You killed the other guy too?
- He went for my gun.

314
00:35:13.572 --> 00:35:16.533
It was self-defence.
Go ahead. call the police.

315
00:35:17.743 --> 00:35:19.661
- No. no...
- I'm taking pictures.

316
00:35:19.786 --> 00:35:21.330
No pictures.

317
00:35:23.165 --> 00:35:24.291
<i>You had a gun!</i>

318
00:35:24.750 --> 00:35:29.421
They only had a knife. You could have
handed them over to the police.

319
00:35:30.297 --> 00:35:33.175
Zasa sent them.
I just sent him a message.

320
00:35:34.343 --> 00:35:39.264
- Now he has to send you one back.
- Zasa is going to send me one back?

321
00:35:39.389 --> 00:35:42.100
He did the right thing.
He got Zasa's name!

322
00:35:42.226 --> 00:35:45.854
<i>What has Joey Zasa to do
with anything? Joey Zasa is a pazzo.</i>

323
00:35:49.399 --> 00:35:51.610
All right. You are what you are.

324
00:35:52.444 --> 00:35:55.197
It's your nature. Stay close to me.

325
00:35:55.322 --> 00:35:59.284
Don't do anything. Keep your mouth
shut and your eyes open.

326
00:35:59.409 --> 00:36:02.120
- And you do what I tell you.
- I understand.

327
00:36:02.246 --> 00:36:05.374
- I have problems with the Commission.
- I know.

328
00:36:05.499 --> 00:36:10.003
- You don't make them easier.
- It wasn't my idea that this happened.

329
00:36:10.921 --> 00:36:13.215
- Get out of here.
- Michael...

330
00:36:13.924 --> 00:36:15.050
Yes?

331
00:36:16.844 --> 00:36:20.305
<i>- Now they'll fear you.
- Maybe they should fear you.</i>

332
00:36:24.142 --> 00:36:27.771
- B.J.. what's up?
- The Archbishop just called back.

333
00:36:27.938 --> 00:36:30.440
We've arranged some amazing things.

334
00:36:30.566 --> 00:36:32.526
The publicity is phenomenal. You're the
new Rockefeller. A philanthropist.

335
00:36:32.568 --> 00:36:34.528
The publicity is phenomenal. You're the
new Rockefeller. A philanthropist.

336
00:36:36.947 --> 00:36:40.033
- Sign here. please.
- Times do change. don't they?

337
00:36:40.701 --> 00:36:45.038
My father hated foundations.
He loved doing it by himself.

338
00:36:46.248 --> 00:36:48.500
Man to man. But we're different.

339
00:36:48.625 --> 00:36:53.964
No different than any large corporation.
We control a lot of money with little.

340
00:36:54.089 --> 00:36:58.260
Minimise taxes.
With no government control.

341
00:37:06.894 --> 00:37:09.313
- Godfather.
- Andrew.

342
00:37:10.689 --> 00:37:15.694
- Off to Rome...
- I wanted to thank you for everything.

343
00:37:16.278 --> 00:37:19.198
- Do you want some breakfast?
- Thanks. I can't.

344
00:37:19.781 --> 00:37:23.494
<i>- How's your Italian?
- Devo fare un po�di pratica.</i>

345
00:37:24.786 --> 00:37:26.914
- His father was a great lawyer.
- I know.

346
00:37:27.039 --> 00:37:31.502
Didn't live to see him ordained. I did.
Did you ever see one of those?

347
00:37:31.627 --> 00:37:34.880
Beautiful. I was so proud.
Let me walk you out.

348
00:37:36.340 --> 00:37:38.675
If you hear any rumours in the Vatican.
let me know.

349
00:37:38.800 --> 00:37:41.178
No. Andrew has the true faith.

350
00:37:50.562 --> 00:37:52.397
<i>Don Corleone.</i>

351
00:37:52.523 --> 00:37:56.360
I need your help. And not just
to light a little candle.

352
00:37:58.028 --> 00:38:04.493
My gift was to be able to persuade
people to give to the Holy Church.

353
00:38:05.661 --> 00:38:09.957
Then Rome decides to put me
in charge of the Vatican Bank...

354
00:38:12.251 --> 00:38:14.920
...but I was never a true banker.

355
00:38:17.965 --> 00:38:21.885
Mea culpa. I trusted my friends.

356
00:38:23.220 --> 00:38:25.097
Friendship and money...

357
00:38:26.181 --> 00:38:27.933
Oil and water...

358
00:38:28.100 --> 00:38:29.226
Indeed.

359
00:38:29.893 --> 00:38:36.275
But these "friends" used the good name
of the Church to feed their greed.

360
00:38:37.568 --> 00:38:39.486
If money was lost...

361
00:38:41.029 --> 00:38:42.781
...then I am to blame.

362
00:38:45.033 --> 00:38:49.538
If only prayer could pay off
our 700 million dollar deficit.

363
00:38:51.665 --> 00:38:53.709
769 million...

364
00:38:59.423 --> 00:39:04.344
The Church owns 25 percent
of a large corporation. Immobiliare.

365
00:39:05.345 --> 00:39:07.306
You know the one I mean?

366
00:39:07.431 --> 00:39:11.727
Largest landlord on Earth.
Real estate worth six billion dollars.

367
00:39:14.104 --> 00:39:15.772
That's true.

368
00:39:16.565 --> 00:39:19.943
And the Vatican vote
is necessary for control.

369
00:39:22.654 --> 00:39:25.115
No. you're mistaken.

370
00:39:25.741 --> 00:39:29.912
This isn't a question of one person
deciding. One deciding vote.

371
00:39:30.037 --> 00:39:35.542
This is like any other company.
We have directors and very old rules.

372
00:39:36.543 --> 00:39:40.339
The Pope himself
would have to approve you.

373
00:39:45.219 --> 00:39:47.012
We've sold the casinos.

374
00:39:48.764 --> 00:39:51.475
All businesses having to do
with gambling.

375
00:39:52.601 --> 00:39:57.898
We have no interests or investments
in anything illegitimate.

376
00:40:00.943 --> 00:40:05.322
The Corleones are prepared to deposit
500 million dollars in the Vatican Bank

377
00:40:05.447 --> 00:40:08.992
when Mr Corleone receives majority
control of Immobiliare.

378
00:40:09.117 --> 00:40:13.789
Immobiliare could be something new.
A European conglomerate.

379
00:40:15.457 --> 00:40:19.127
Few families have control
of such a company.

380
00:40:22.381 --> 00:40:24.675
It seems that. in today's world.

381
00:40:25.342 --> 00:40:29.346
the power to absolve debt is greater
than the power of forgiveness.

382
00:40:31.557 --> 00:40:33.308
600 million dollars.

383
00:40:38.188 --> 00:40:41.066
Don't overestimate
the power of forgiveness.

384
00:40:43.402 --> 00:40:45.070
Don Corleone.

385
00:40:45.195 --> 00:40:49.575
this deal with Immobiliare can make you
one of the richest men in the world.

386
00:40:50.325 --> 00:40:55.247
Your whole past history. and the history
of your family. would be washed away.

387
00:40:59.418 --> 00:41:00.919
600 million.

388
00:41:16.476 --> 00:41:20.314
<i>The motion under discussion
relates to Corleone Group's proposal</i>

389
00:41:21.440 --> 00:41:26.195
<i>to acquire 100.000.000 newly issued
Class A voting shares.</i>

390
00:41:28.947 --> 00:41:33.619
<i>... Corleone capital invested directly
into International Immobiliare.</i>

391
00:41:34.786 --> 00:41:37.998
<i>an old and respected
European company.</i>

392
00:41:38.874 --> 00:41:41.585
Mr Corleone has
an ambitious programme

393
00:41:41.710 --> 00:41:44.171
to expand this real estate company

394
00:41:44.338 --> 00:41:46.840
into an international conglomerate...

395
00:41:49.927 --> 00:41:55.724
...by Eastern techniques of efficiency
and focus and unlimited...

396
00:41:55.849 --> 00:41:57.768
Mr Corleone. excuse me.

397
00:41:58.310 --> 00:42:01.480
Didn't you recently deposit 200 million
in the Vatican Bank.

398
00:42:01.605 --> 00:42:04.858
which is affiliated with Immobiliare?

399
00:42:04.983 --> 00:42:06.360
True. Why not?

400
00:42:06.485 --> 00:42:12.658
Wasn't there any questioning about
the timing on this particular deposit?

401
00:42:12.783 --> 00:42:14.827
Mr Chairman. if I may?

402
00:42:16.411 --> 00:42:20.624
The Vito Andolini Corleone Foundation.
of which Mary Corleone is chairman.

403
00:42:20.749 --> 00:42:24.044
has made an endowment
of 100 million dollars.

404
00:42:24.169 --> 00:42:28.298
The money comes from his own family
and will be administered by the Vatican.

405
00:42:28.382 --> 00:42:30.592
Does that answer your question?

406
00:42:31.134 --> 00:42:37.140
I have always believed that helping your
fellow man is profitable in every sense.

407
00:42:37.641 --> 00:42:39.643
personally and bottom line.

408
00:42:40.394 --> 00:42:45.774
My fellow shareholders. if Europe
and America can learn to co-operate.

409
00:42:45.899 --> 00:42:50.028
if we can learn to pool our wealth.
share our markets.

410
00:42:50.154 --> 00:42:55.159
we can defeat any competition
anywhere in the world.

411
00:42:55.284 --> 00:42:57.619
Thank you for your time.

412
00:42:57.744 --> 00:43:02.291
I hope that you will look favourably
on my proposal. Thank you.

413
00:43:08.130 --> 00:43:10.465
Let me have this microphone here.

414
00:43:10.591 --> 00:43:16.054
Will we let a criminal run our company?
He's got the map of Sicily on his face!

415
00:43:16.180 --> 00:43:17.306
Order!

416
00:43:17.431 --> 00:43:20.017
He's either a Catholic or a mafioso...

417
00:43:22.477 --> 00:43:26.064
The Hamilton Investors Group
cannot support this proposal.

418
00:43:27.441 --> 00:43:29.151
Your Excellency...

419
00:43:30.068 --> 00:43:31.570
Mr Chairman...

420
00:43:32.070 --> 00:43:37.534
...the Vatican Bank feels
that International Immobiliare...

421
00:43:39.745 --> 00:43:43.290
...will be safe in Mr Corleone's hands.

422
00:43:44.082 --> 00:43:48.795
...subject to audit and final ratification.
which must take place in Rome.

423
00:43:48.921 --> 00:43:52.090
Please join me in welcoming
Mr Michael Corleone.

424
00:44:02.476 --> 00:44:03.602
Dad?

425
00:44:06.355 --> 00:44:09.233
Tony says that I'm a front
for the foundation.

426
00:44:11.193 --> 00:44:13.904
That you're using me to pull the strings.

427
00:44:14.655 --> 00:44:17.491
- To get the money where you want it.
- Please!

428
00:44:17.991 --> 00:44:20.828
- To shine up your public image.
- Mary!

429
00:44:21.954 --> 00:44:25.290
Mary. this is real.
This foundation is real.

430
00:44:28.168 --> 00:44:32.923
I wanted Anthony to be part of it.
I thought you would be together on this.

431
00:44:33.048 --> 00:44:37.261
I won't interfere.
I'll help. but only if you ask.

432
00:44:37.386 --> 00:44:39.221
What is this really for?

433
00:44:40.138 --> 00:44:43.141
Why are you doing this?
Why am I doing this?

434
00:44:44.935 --> 00:44:49.314
I'm doing this for my children.
You're doing it for your children too.

435
00:44:50.315 --> 00:44:53.318
This foundation is supposed to
help all people.

436
00:44:53.443 --> 00:44:55.696
That's the purpose.

437
00:44:55.821 --> 00:45:00.159
This is legitimate.
Mary. I swear. this is legitimate.

438
00:45:04.288 --> 00:45:07.082
Dad. I want this to bring me
closer to you.

439
00:45:15.257 --> 00:45:18.760
I would burn in hell to keep you safe.

440
00:45:32.441 --> 00:45:35.360
Go in the other car.
I'll ride with Michael.

441
00:45:35.486 --> 00:45:36.987
Go. go. go.

442
00:45:50.542 --> 00:45:55.714
As your family's oldest friend. I'm
always chosen to bring you messages.

443
00:45:58.467 --> 00:46:00.511
Tell me. Don Altobello.

444
00:46:03.013 --> 00:46:07.601
Your old partners are grateful for
the money you made them.

445
00:46:07.726 --> 00:46:09.394
They worship you...

446
00:46:10.145 --> 00:46:15.943
...but their hearts are broken. because
they think you abandoned them.

447
00:46:16.735 --> 00:46:22.741
They want to share your deal
on Immobiliare. to be a family again.

448
00:46:22.866 --> 00:46:25.244
It can purify their money.

449
00:46:27.538 --> 00:46:29.164
This I cannot do.

450
00:46:32.000 --> 00:46:34.628
Immobiliare must be legitimate.

451
00:46:37.047 --> 00:46:38.173
I know.

452
00:46:39.258 --> 00:46:41.134
But they're unhappy.

453
00:46:43.220 --> 00:46:44.471
And you?

454
00:46:45.472 --> 00:46:50.602
I ask nothing for myself.
Only peace in my old age.

455
00:46:51.186 --> 00:46:54.106
But I must please the world around me.

456
00:46:56.191 --> 00:47:01.780
Michael. your father was
a reasonable man. Learn from him.

457
00:47:04.241 --> 00:47:07.244
I learnt many things from my father.

458
00:47:12.708 --> 00:47:17.963
Call a meeting. my friend.
so there are no debts or grudges.

459
00:47:19.214 --> 00:47:21.884
We will make the peace. you and I.

460
00:47:38.317 --> 00:47:41.028
<i>The Vatican announced today...</i>

461
00:47:41.195 --> 00:47:44.781
<i>that Pope Paul VI has cancelled
his Sunday blessing...</i>

462
00:47:44.948 --> 00:47:46.658
<i>due to ill health.</i>

463
00:47:46.867 --> 00:47:49.661
<i>His physician has ordered
total bedrest...</i>

464
00:47:49.953 --> 00:47:52.539
<i>and cessation of all activities.</i>

465
00:48:00.255 --> 00:48:02.132
They've had a press conference.

466
00:48:02.299 --> 00:48:05.260
<i>The Pope's condition
is grave. "Gravissimo."</i>

467
00:48:32.996 --> 00:48:36.291
The purpose of this meeting
is to ratify...

468
00:48:36.542 --> 00:48:39.878
the motion passed by our
shareholders in New York.

469
00:48:41.380 --> 00:48:42.589
Please...

470
00:48:43.549 --> 00:48:47.928
Our group represents a consortium
of Catholic businessmen

471
00:48:48.053 --> 00:48:50.764
against the Corleone control.

472
00:48:51.723 --> 00:48:56.728
The Vatican has cast its vote. Corleone
Group already controls the Board.

473
00:48:56.854 --> 00:49:01.233
According to the Lateran Treaty.
the Vatican vote must be ratified here.

474
00:49:01.358 --> 00:49:03.360
Here in Rome. by the Pope.

475
00:49:07.322 --> 00:49:10.284
The Pope is gravely ill.

476
00:49:11.743 --> 00:49:15.122
Until he recovers. I am powerless.

477
00:49:16.415 --> 00:49:19.251
- What if he dies?
- Then...

478
00:49:20.085 --> 00:49:23.380
...as you Americans say. all bets are off.

479
00:49:23.505 --> 00:49:25.299
Gentlemen. please.

480
00:49:26.717 --> 00:49:29.887
This is a brief delay. Nothing more.

481
00:49:34.850 --> 00:49:36.977
Your Excellency. gentlemen...

482
00:49:38.228 --> 00:49:43.192
I advise you to join us in our prayers
for the Holy Father's recovery.

483
00:49:44.735 --> 00:49:46.445
We had an agreement!

484
00:49:47.613 --> 00:49:51.200
This meeting was to be
merely a formality.

485
00:49:51.325 --> 00:49:56.455
- Please sit down.
- I'd rather stand. Give me an answer.

486
00:49:56.580 --> 00:50:01.877
The Immobiliare has its roots in the
European tradition. Please understand.

487
00:50:02.628 --> 00:50:05.839
I understand.
Your tactics are despicable.

488
00:50:05.964 --> 00:50:08.926
That's quite an indictment.
coming from a Corleone.

489
00:50:09.051 --> 00:50:13.096
- Gentlemen. gentlemen!
- Remember you are in the Vatican.

490
00:50:16.934 --> 00:50:22.314
- What is it that you want?
- Yes. you will take control.

491
00:50:23.440 --> 00:50:26.735
We'll gladly put you at the helm
of our little fleet.

492
00:50:27.361 --> 00:50:30.989
but our ships must all sail
in the same direction.

493
00:50:32.574 --> 00:50:37.871
Otherwise. who can say how long
your stay with us will last?

494
00:50:40.040 --> 00:50:45.629
It's not personal. It's only business.
You should know. Godfather.

495
00:50:49.508 --> 00:50:50.759
Very well.

496
00:50:52.177 --> 00:50:56.890
You want to do business with me?
I will do business with you.

497
00:50:57.933 --> 00:50:59.726
Vipers. all of them.

498
00:51:05.607 --> 00:51:08.527
- We're back with the Borgias!
- Uncle Michael...

499
00:51:08.652 --> 00:51:11.738
- Andrew!
- I heard you were here.

500
00:51:11.864 --> 00:51:15.242
It's so nice to see you.
Vincent. it's so nice.

501
00:51:16.118 --> 00:51:19.329
What is this about the Borgias?
Those days are over.

502
00:51:24.543 --> 00:51:26.503
- Recognise it?
- Yeah.

503
00:51:28.130 --> 00:51:32.634
Genco Olive Oil. That's where our
grandfather started as a delivery boy.

504
00:51:34.011 --> 00:51:36.180
Three years later he owned it.

505
00:51:36.305 --> 00:51:38.390
- Only in America.
- That's it.

506
00:51:39.433 --> 00:51:44.313
Vincenzo. where have you been hiding?
We need your help so badly.

507
00:51:44.438 --> 00:51:47.941
- What can I do for you?
- Get rid of Joe Zasa. He sells drugs...

508
00:51:48.066 --> 00:51:52.863
Now that I'm an older woman.
I'm afraid to go out at night.

509
00:51:52.988 --> 00:51:55.240
Where should they be now?

510
00:51:55.365 --> 00:51:58.285
- Lou. what's going on?
- We're late.

511
00:52:00.329 --> 00:52:02.789
- Have I ever let you down?
- I trust you.

512
00:52:02.915 --> 00:52:05.167
- Don't worry.
- Thank you.

513
00:52:05.292 --> 00:52:06.877
Enjoy yourselves.

514
00:52:13.342 --> 00:52:16.929
- What was that?
- The neighbourhood's in trouble.

515
00:52:18.013 --> 00:52:20.682
- Do you keep an eye out for them?
- Yes.

516
00:52:20.807 --> 00:52:23.227
- And for me?
- From now on.

517
00:52:24.436 --> 00:52:28.232
- I've missed you all this time.
- I missed you too. cousin.

518
00:52:28.357 --> 00:52:32.861
I missed growing up with my cousins.
I didn't even know you. but missed you.

519
00:52:34.154 --> 00:52:38.534
Do you remember stories about
our fathers? The old days?

520
00:52:38.659 --> 00:52:40.869
Yeah. what do you want to know?

521
00:52:43.121 --> 00:52:48.210
- What was Sonny like?
- Well. he was the Prince of the City.

522
00:52:49.711 --> 00:52:53.173
He died before I was born.
but I've heard a lot about him.

523
00:52:54.925 --> 00:52:58.220
- What about my father?
- He's a great man.

524
00:52:59.721 --> 00:53:02.015
He's a hero. He saved the family.

525
00:53:03.976 --> 00:53:05.602
- Vincent?
- What?

526
00:53:05.727 --> 00:53:07.855
Did he kill his own brother?

527
00:53:12.025 --> 00:53:13.110
No.

528
00:53:15.612 --> 00:53:17.197
So. it's all lies?

529
00:53:21.660 --> 00:53:24.621
Just stories. sweetheart. Okay?

530
00:53:28.625 --> 00:53:29.751
Okay.

531
00:53:31.503 --> 00:53:33.005
I believe you.

532
00:53:34.214 --> 00:53:37.384
- I'm glad you're around.
- I'm glad you're here too.

533
00:53:42.139 --> 00:53:43.515
<i>Cugina...</i>

534
00:53:44.516 --> 00:53:45.851
Cous...

535
00:53:59.698 --> 00:54:03.160
I'd like to take Joey Zasa for a ride
in this and drop him.

536
00:54:03.285 --> 00:54:05.329
Joey Zasa is nothing.

537
00:54:06.205 --> 00:54:09.750
He's a small time enforcer.
He bluffs and threatens.

538
00:54:09.875 --> 00:54:13.420
He's nothing.
You can see him coming a mile away.

539
00:54:14.379 --> 00:54:16.840
- We should kill him before he...
- No!

540
00:54:19.927 --> 00:54:23.847
Never hate your enemies.
It affects your judgement.

541
00:54:39.571 --> 00:54:42.032
Nice to see you again. Mr Corleone.

542
00:55:01.301 --> 00:55:03.554
Hey. girls. Let's go.

543
00:55:20.988 --> 00:55:25.159
We trusted you to manage
our money in the casinos.

544
00:55:25.284 --> 00:55:30.914
It's not even 20 years. You've sold the
casinos and made fortunes for all of us.

545
00:55:31.039 --> 00:55:33.083
Bravo. Don Corleone!

546
00:55:35.252 --> 00:55:36.545
Thank you.

547
00:55:37.504 --> 00:55:43.927
Friends. I have come here
because our business together is done.

548
00:55:45.554 --> 00:55:47.181
We have prospered.

549
00:55:47.306 --> 00:55:52.186
and now it is time for us to dissolve
the business relationship between us.

550
00:55:54.396 --> 00:55:55.814
That's it.

551
00:55:55.939 --> 00:55:59.026
But I do have a little surprise. Al?

552
00:56:02.070 --> 00:56:04.072
Your shares in the casinos.

553
00:56:04.740 --> 00:56:08.535
I thought I cut through all the red tape.
so you could get your money right away.

554
00:56:14.750 --> 00:56:17.002
50 million dollars!

555
00:56:17.127 --> 00:56:20.422
- Not everybody gets the same.
- Nothing for you...

556
00:56:20.547 --> 00:56:25.302
- It depends on your investment.
- Michael. this is really generous!

557
00:56:26.345 --> 00:56:27.679
Wonderful!

558
00:56:30.641 --> 00:56:34.937
- Parisi. how much did you invest?
- I don't remember.

559
00:56:35.771 --> 00:56:37.356
You're blessed.

560
00:56:42.152 --> 00:56:46.657
My family has done much of
the hard work. taken many risks.

561
00:56:48.867 --> 00:56:51.870
All to make money
for the rest of the families.

562
00:56:54.206 --> 00:56:56.124
You all know Joey Zasa.

563
00:56:57.084 --> 00:56:59.378
He is. I admit. an important man.

564
00:57:00.420 --> 00:57:03.966
His picture is on the cover
of the New York Times magazine.

565
00:57:04.633 --> 00:57:08.470
He gets the Esquire Magazine award
for the best dressed gangster.

566
00:57:09.638 --> 00:57:11.431
The newspapers praise him

567
00:57:11.557 --> 00:57:15.853
because he hires Blacks.
which shows he has a good heart.

568
00:57:18.438 --> 00:57:19.940
He is famous.

569
00:57:20.732 --> 00:57:26.572
Who knows? Maybe one day
he'll make all of you popular.

570
00:57:28.240 --> 00:57:29.324
It's true.

571
00:57:29.449 --> 00:57:34.830
<i>I make more of a bella figura.
That is my nature.</i>

572
00:57:34.955 --> 00:57:39.751
But I also want to make a move
into legitimate enterprises.

573
00:57:39.877 --> 00:57:42.421
I'd like a little pin from the Pope.

574
00:57:42.963 --> 00:57:47.801
Sure. I take the Blacks
and the Spanish into my family.

575
00:57:47.926 --> 00:57:51.180
because that's America.

576
00:57:51.972 --> 00:57:55.142
And you guarantee
that they don't deal drugs?

577
00:57:56.977 --> 00:58:01.356
I don't guarantee that. I guarantee
that I'll kill anybody who does.

578
00:58:05.861 --> 00:58:10.741
- Let me talk to him.
- Who can refuse Don Altobello?

579
00:58:11.283 --> 00:58:13.410
- Joey. are you...
- No!

580
00:58:14.244 --> 00:58:19.333
I say to all of you. I have been
treated this day with no respect.

581
00:58:20.501 --> 00:58:25.714
I've earned you all money.
I've made you rich and I asked for little.

582
00:58:25.839 --> 00:58:29.468
Good. You will not give. so I'll take!

583
00:58:30.802 --> 00:58:33.180
As for Don Corleone.

584
00:58:33.305 --> 00:58:38.977
he makes it very clear to me today
that he is my enemy.

585
00:58:42.856 --> 00:58:44.900
You must choose between us.

586
00:58:49.446 --> 00:58:50.489
No. Joey!

587
00:58:52.074 --> 00:58:54.660
Michael. we could reason together.

588
00:58:55.244 --> 00:58:56.495
No.

589
00:58:57.830 --> 00:59:01.625
Michael. please... let's agree.

590
00:59:02.292 --> 00:59:04.461
He doesn't know what he's...

591
00:59:04.586 --> 00:59:05.921
No. no.

592
00:59:10.801 --> 00:59:13.387
Michael. the news is everywhere.

593
00:59:14.304 --> 00:59:18.225
Everyone says that you
control Immobiliare.

594
00:59:18.350 --> 00:59:23.188
Immobiliare is already laundering
money in Peru and Nassau.

595
00:59:24.439 --> 00:59:28.652
We've worked with you for 40 years.
We should wet our beaks a little.

596
00:59:28.819 --> 00:59:33.490
- We want to do business with you.
- That's right. we've been together...

597
00:59:43.125 --> 00:59:46.253
- It's a hit! Let's go!
- Let's get out of here! Move!

598
01:00:04.771 --> 01:00:07.107
My coat! It's my lucky coat!

599
01:00:08.275 --> 01:00:09.985
It's my lucky coat!

600
01:00:15.949 --> 01:00:17.284
Stay behind me!

601
01:00:32.799 --> 01:00:34.843
Mikey. this way!

602
01:00:42.935 --> 01:00:45.938
Zasa. you son-of-a-bitch...

603
01:01:05.666 --> 01:01:07.835
Come on. We're out of here.

604
01:01:38.740 --> 01:01:40.951
<i>- You did good. Vincent.
- Grazie.</i>

605
01:01:41.368 --> 01:01:44.413
The old Dons were pretty much
wiped out.

606
01:01:44.580 --> 01:01:47.666
The survivors made deals with Zasa.

607
01:01:48.834 --> 01:01:51.170
- Altobello?
- He survived.

608
01:01:51.295 --> 01:01:55.924
He's with his daughters in Staten Island.
He says he's going to retire in Sicily.

609
01:01:57.801 --> 01:02:02.097
Joey Zasa would never pull something
like this without the backing.

610
01:02:02.931 --> 01:02:08.353
He�s just muscle. He doesn't have
the wit for that helicopter attack.

611
01:02:08.479 --> 01:02:12.649
He doesn't even have the ambition
to wipe out the whole Commission.

612
01:02:12.774 --> 01:02:15.360
I say we hit back and take Zasa out!

613
01:02:20.782 --> 01:02:23.619
Never let anyone know
what you're thinking.

614
01:02:31.293 --> 01:02:34.129
Let's get a message to Joey Zasa.

615
01:02:37.257 --> 01:02:39.426
I respect what he's done.

616
01:02:40.552 --> 01:02:43.305
The new overthrows the old. It's natural.

617
01:02:43.805 --> 01:02:46.266
How can you do business with this guy?

618
01:02:48.685 --> 01:02:52.523
I'm a businessman. first and foremost.
I want no further conflict.

619
01:02:52.648 --> 01:02:56.777
- Tell him that he can live or he can die.
- Vincent. will you shut up!

620
01:03:14.628 --> 01:03:16.046
That's it.

621
01:03:18.215 --> 01:03:19.591
Joey Zasa...

622
01:03:20.300 --> 01:03:22.553
He can't be doing this alone.

623
01:03:26.181 --> 01:03:29.893
Just when I thought I was out.
they pull me back in.

624
01:03:38.402 --> 01:03:43.740
Our true enemy has not yet
shown his face.

625
01:03:47.953 --> 01:03:49.163
Michael!

626
01:03:55.752 --> 01:03:59.131
- Has he had his medicine?
- I don't know what he took.

627
01:04:04.469 --> 01:04:06.638
- I've got my wind back.
- Call a doctor.

628
01:04:06.763 --> 01:04:08.599
- Run. run. run!
- Vincent!

629
01:04:08.724 --> 01:04:12.478
Run at thunder. girl! Thunder can't hurt!

630
01:04:12.603 --> 01:04:14.521
Harmless noise!

631
01:04:15.272 --> 01:04:19.860
Bullshit! You deceitful old fuck!

632
01:04:20.569 --> 01:04:23.071
Altobello. you fuck!

633
01:04:25.824 --> 01:04:27.034
Fredo!

634
01:04:27.993 --> 01:04:29.495
Fredo!

635
01:04:52.226 --> 01:04:54.561
Oh. God! Dad!

636
01:04:57.022 --> 01:04:58.607
Excuse me.

637
01:04:59.233 --> 01:05:00.734
I'll call Kay.

638
01:05:11.036 --> 01:05:14.540
- Good evening. sir.
- Can we wait here? We'll be back soon.

639
01:05:21.129 --> 01:05:26.760
Mr Harrison. you said it was urgent.
Have you come to confess your sins?

640
01:05:27.386 --> 01:05:31.849
Michael Corleone has had a diabetic
stroke. I wanted you to know about it.

641
01:05:32.558 --> 01:05:37.437
He's in a coma. I'm here to insist
the deal goes through in any event.

642
01:05:37.563 --> 01:05:39.815
The Pope has not much time left.

643
01:05:41.066 --> 01:05:44.570
So. as you. I am in a difficult position.

644
01:05:45.028 --> 01:05:48.073
We have to ratify this deal
as soon as possible.

645
01:05:48.991 --> 01:05:51.660
- We have an understanding.
- Good.

646
01:05:53.036 --> 01:05:56.456
- I'm going to the hospital.
- I'll pray for Mr Corleone.

647
01:06:01.086 --> 01:06:04.631
- Our thoughts are with Mr Corleone.
- Thank you. Father Jim.

648
01:06:07.217 --> 01:06:10.429
Everything will be out in the open
if Corleone dies.

649
01:06:12.097 --> 01:06:14.057
Play for time. Keinszig.

650
01:06:14.850 --> 01:06:18.979
A habit born of
a long contemplation of eternity.

651
01:06:25.777 --> 01:06:29.448
- Forget about it. Vinnie.
- Why? It's a simple hit.

652
01:06:29.573 --> 01:06:35.204
I'd love to smack Joey Zasa and then
whack the fag. But it's impossible.

653
01:06:35.621 --> 01:06:40.834
He's always with people. in front of
TV cameras in his own neighbourhood.

654
01:06:40.959 --> 01:06:43.837
- It's not impossible. It'll work for us.
- How?

655
01:06:44.505 --> 01:06:48.467
Do you think he's going to let
Uncle Michael survive? Would you?

656
01:06:49.426 --> 01:06:51.428
He may not survive anyway.

657
01:06:52.596 --> 01:06:55.224
- How would you do it?
- I'd do it myself.

658
01:06:57.810 --> 01:06:58.977
Do it!

659
01:07:01.188 --> 01:07:03.982
- What would you need?
- A couple of guys.

660
01:07:33.804 --> 01:07:35.305
Hello. Michael.

661
01:07:38.475 --> 01:07:39.726
It's Kay.

662
01:07:44.815 --> 01:07:45.899
Kay...

663
01:07:48.235 --> 01:07:50.112
I never expected you.

664
01:07:51.071 --> 01:07:53.115
No. I know.

665
01:07:55.534 --> 01:07:57.119
But I'm here.

666
01:08:01.039 --> 01:08:02.875
- I'm glad.
- You know...

667
01:08:06.211 --> 01:08:08.922
I've never seen you looking so helpless.

668
01:08:12.926 --> 01:08:14.887
It's not so bad. really.

669
01:08:16.847 --> 01:08:20.642
I feel... I'm getting wiser now.

670
01:08:21.185 --> 01:08:23.020
- Yeah.
- Oh. yeah.

671
01:08:24.354 --> 01:08:29.568
- The sicker you get. the wiser you get?
- When I'm dead. I'll be really smart.

672
01:08:31.361 --> 01:08:35.240
Michael... I want to thank you for Tony.

673
01:08:38.452 --> 01:08:42.206
He's doing really well.
He's gotten some very good notices.

674
01:08:42.706 --> 01:08:47.544
and he'll make his operatic debut
in Sicily. in Palermo this Easter. so...

675
01:08:49.505 --> 01:08:50.547
So. thank you.

676
01:08:52.341 --> 01:08:55.093
That's a real honour. In Sicily.

677
01:09:00.140 --> 01:09:02.893
I will be there. I won't miss that.

678
01:09:03.727 --> 01:09:05.437
I won't miss that.

679
01:09:11.568 --> 01:09:13.695
Mary. Tony...

680
01:09:15.197 --> 01:09:16.615
Go see Dad.

681
01:09:22.579 --> 01:09:25.582
- Sweetheart!
- Everything's going to be all right.

682
01:09:26.458 --> 01:09:28.627
- Tony!
- How are you doing. Pop?

683
01:09:31.088 --> 01:09:34.049
Your mother told me what happened.

684
01:09:34.174 --> 01:09:39.304
- About Palermo? I hope you'll be there.
- Of course. Kiss me.

685
01:09:58.490 --> 01:10:02.661
<i>- Cousin Vinnie?
- He's not here. Call his apartment.</i>

686
01:10:04.663 --> 01:10:07.082
- It's your cousin Mary.
- Let her in.

687
01:10:11.670 --> 01:10:15.632
Hi. cous. I thought I'd drop by.
Is that okay?

688
01:10:15.757 --> 01:10:17.509
I'll get the guys.

689
01:10:19.428 --> 01:10:22.473
No. it's not okay.
You shouldn't have come. Mary.

690
01:10:23.807 --> 01:10:26.059
Only a couple of minutes. okay?

691
01:10:27.519 --> 01:10:30.355
- You look beautiful. cous.
- Thanks.

692
01:10:33.192 --> 01:10:35.652
So this is your club. your hideout?

693
01:10:36.361 --> 01:10:38.864
- Yeah.
- I came here to check it out.

694
01:10:43.869 --> 01:10:47.664
It's so strange. just me
and Aunt Connie in the house.

695
01:10:47.789 --> 01:10:51.835
- I feel better when I'm with you.
- What's wrong. sweetheart?

696
01:10:52.503 --> 01:10:55.172
- I'm scared about my father.
- Don't be.

697
01:10:55.297 --> 01:10:58.967
When they took him out of
the ambulance. I thought he was dead.

698
01:10:59.092 --> 01:11:01.762
Everybody says he's going to be better.

699
01:11:03.722 --> 01:11:05.224
Don't worry.

700
01:11:05.766 --> 01:11:08.310
I remember a shooting when I was little.

701
01:11:09.478 --> 01:11:14.066
And one time Al Neri and other
bodyguards took me and Tony away.

702
01:11:16.026 --> 01:11:18.070
Is it all happening again?

703
01:11:19.655 --> 01:11:21.532
Not like that. sweetie.

704
01:11:23.033 --> 01:11:26.620
Then why are you hiding here?
Is something going to happen to you?

705
01:11:28.539 --> 01:11:32.292
<i>Nothing's going to happen
to me. cugina. We'll take care of you.</i>

706
01:11:43.220 --> 01:11:47.349
- Can I stay here and hide out with you?
- Can you help me cook for the boys?

707
01:11:47.474 --> 01:11:50.978
You know that I don't know
how to cook. but I'll help.

708
01:12:03.574 --> 01:12:04.700
Okay...

709
01:12:05.659 --> 01:12:07.077
What do I do?

710
01:12:38.108 --> 01:12:40.861
- I love you. cous.
- I love you. too. cous.

711
01:12:44.698 --> 01:12:46.116
Let us cook.

712
01:13:02.424 --> 01:13:03.675
Hold me.

713
01:13:39.086 --> 01:13:43.423
You in the press and the police
use words like "Mafia". "Cosa Nostra".

714
01:13:43.549 --> 01:13:48.804
This is a fantasy. We Italian-Americans
laid the bricks that built this city.

715
01:13:48.929 --> 01:13:51.598
We have Meucci.
who invented the telephone.

716
01:13:51.723 --> 01:13:55.435
We have Don Ameche.
who played the guy who invented it.

717
01:13:56.103 --> 01:14:00.065
Buy yourself a raffle ticket.
maybe you'll win a Cadillac.

718
01:14:00.691 --> 01:14:02.943
The salsiccia is wonderful!

719
01:14:03.068 --> 01:14:04.862
Here. have a sandwich.

720
01:14:17.249 --> 01:14:20.169
- Nice to see you. Mr Zasa.
- Have a nice time.

721
01:14:21.879 --> 01:14:24.131
Don't forget to buy your raffle tickets.

722
01:14:27.426 --> 01:14:30.053
- What are you doing?
- He didn't mean it.

723
01:14:30.846 --> 01:14:33.515
- Tell him you're sorry.
- Okay. let's go.

724
01:14:51.700 --> 01:14:54.912
Joey! How are you?

725
01:14:55.037 --> 01:14:56.830
How are you. Buddy boy?

726
01:14:57.873 --> 01:15:00.667
Hey. Joey Zasa! Joey. up your ass!

727
01:15:02.711 --> 01:15:05.797
- Who is this? Do you know him?
- Ignore him.

728
01:15:06.757 --> 01:15:09.676
Who's going to win the car? The Ant?

729
01:15:10.761 --> 01:15:14.890
<i>This is what gives Italian-Americans
a bad name. A cappone like this.</i>

730
01:15:15.265 --> 01:15:17.851
Joey. up your ass!

731
01:15:17.976 --> 01:15:21.230
Get off the car!
Do you have a raffle ticket?

732
01:15:21.355 --> 01:15:24.066
Joey. take a look at my raffle ticket!

733
01:15:24.566 --> 01:15:28.654
Here's what I think of you...
and your raffle ticket.

734
01:15:29.238 --> 01:15:32.699
Get the fuck off this car.
I'll break your fucking balls.

735
01:15:35.494 --> 01:15:37.204
Get out of here!

736
01:15:52.052 --> 01:15:54.388
Run. Joey! You piece of shit!

737
01:16:06.900 --> 01:16:08.652
Open the door!

738
01:16:08.777 --> 01:16:10.404
How are you. Joe?

739
01:16:13.699 --> 01:16:14.783
Zasa!

740
01:16:31.550 --> 01:16:38.140
Don't ever again give that kind of order.
Not while I'm alive.

741
01:16:38.265 --> 01:16:39.600
Understand?

742
01:16:41.435 --> 01:16:47.357
You were too sick to make a decision.
I got a go-ahead from Neri and Connie.

743
01:16:48.442 --> 01:16:49.568
Connie?

744
01:16:58.994 --> 01:17:01.580
It was the right decision. Uncle Mike.

745
01:17:02.331 --> 01:17:06.001
It was the wrong decision.
I command this family!

746
01:17:06.460 --> 01:17:08.295
Right or wrong...

747
01:17:09.171 --> 01:17:11.715
...it was not what I wanted!

748
01:17:29.691 --> 01:17:31.318
Do you understand?

749
01:17:38.033 --> 01:17:39.034
Yes.

750
01:17:45.582 --> 01:17:47.292
Come on. Michael.

751
01:17:58.345 --> 01:17:59.638
Yes.

752
01:18:01.682 --> 01:18:07.271
Good. Vincent. help me to my bed.
I want to talk to you alone for a minute.

753
01:18:15.487 --> 01:18:18.866
You know.
I always felt responsible for you.

754
01:18:20.159 --> 01:18:21.702
You know that.

755
01:18:22.619 --> 01:18:24.121
Your father...

756
01:18:25.247 --> 01:18:28.083
...my brother. we were opposites.

757
01:18:28.750 --> 01:18:32.796
We would fight and argue.
But I never doubted his love.

758
01:18:33.714 --> 01:18:37.718
He would do anything for me.
But his temper...

759
01:18:41.388 --> 01:18:44.975
Too much. It clouded his reason.

760
01:18:46.685 --> 01:18:49.188
I don't want you to make that mistake.

761
01:18:51.982 --> 01:18:53.150
Also...

762
01:18:54.193 --> 01:18:56.570
...he. too. had a way with women.

763
01:18:58.572 --> 01:19:00.991
- Vincent...
- So I hear.

764
01:19:01.116 --> 01:19:03.410
What are you doing with my daughter?

765
01:19:06.038 --> 01:19:08.248
What are you doing with her?

766
01:19:12.419 --> 01:19:14.213
It's too dangerous.

767
01:19:17.216 --> 01:19:18.801
Do you hear me?

768
01:19:24.681 --> 01:19:25.766
Okay.

769
01:19:39.655 --> 01:19:41.114
Vincenzo...

770
01:19:45.077 --> 01:19:48.789
When they come.
they'll come at what you love.

771
01:19:57.047 --> 01:19:59.508
Michael. you must lead another life.

772
01:20:00.259 --> 01:20:04.596
You have everything a man
could desire. It's time for you to retire.

773
01:20:06.431 --> 01:20:08.767
I have too much responsibility.

774
01:20:09.977 --> 01:20:15.399
Immobiliare? It's too difficult now.
You should really get out.

775
01:20:15.524 --> 01:20:19.820
<i>What do you know
about those pezzi da novanta in Italy?</i>

776
01:20:23.907 --> 01:20:27.077
I'm too old to know anything
about those new people.

777
01:20:27.661 --> 01:20:31.540
I must accept my age
and grow my olives and tomatoes.

778
01:20:33.458 --> 01:20:36.753
- We're not that old.
- But you're very ill.

779
01:20:37.963 --> 01:20:41.758
Michael... Let me see
what can be done.

780
01:20:42.926 --> 01:20:45.846
Let me work to make your path
a little easier.

781
01:20:47.222 --> 01:20:51.977
- Your friendship does that always.
- That makes me happy.

782
01:20:52.603 --> 01:20:56.523
Joey Zasa...
You were wrong about him.

783
01:20:57.858 --> 01:21:00.944
I trust too much.
That's always been my fault.

784
01:21:08.577 --> 01:21:11.872
Michael... treachery is everywhere.

785
01:21:12.539 --> 01:21:15.834
You still have your fingers
on the strings. even now.

786
01:21:17.961 --> 01:21:20.047
Let's see more of each other.

787
01:21:20.839 --> 01:21:24.968
- Michael. in Sicily?
- In Sicily.

788
01:21:25.928 --> 01:21:27.679
<i>In Sicilia.</i>

789
01:21:28.347 --> 01:21:29.765
<i>In Sicilia.</i>

790
01:22:15.936 --> 01:22:17.271
How are you?

791
01:22:18.105 --> 01:22:20.774
Don Bendino. my old friend.

792
01:22:50.888 --> 01:22:55.809
I brought you here. so that my old friend
and protector. Don Tommasino.

793
01:22:56.351 --> 01:22:57.936
could advise us.

794
01:22:59.563 --> 01:23:02.691
What do you think about Altobello?

795
01:23:03.609 --> 01:23:06.195
A very talented man.

796
01:23:06.737 --> 01:23:10.491
He has kept the peace between our
Sicilian and American friends.

797
01:23:11.408 --> 01:23:13.577
The saint of reason.

798
01:23:15.579 --> 01:23:19.208
A blood bath in Atlantic City
left New York a mess.

799
01:23:20.375 --> 01:23:22.794
Joey Zasa at least was running
a tight ship.

800
01:23:22.920 --> 01:23:26.548
but with him out of the picture
we must step in.

801
01:23:26.673 --> 01:23:30.302
- Step back in...
- Or the Chinese and Colombians will.

802
01:23:31.094 --> 01:23:35.724
The Corleones left drugs. so New York
is weak. and Palermo is strong.

803
01:23:37.226 --> 01:23:41.104
Your enemies always get strong
on what you leave behind.

804
01:23:43.565 --> 01:23:47.820
Who could give the order
for that massacre...

805
01:23:49.696 --> 01:23:53.450
and still pressure the Vatican deal?

806
01:23:53.659 --> 01:23:58.539
Only Lucchesi can reach
between these two worlds.

807
01:24:00.707 --> 01:24:04.002
"Our ships must all sail
in the same direction"...

808
01:24:05.587 --> 01:24:11.176
Italian politics have had these men
for centuries. They are the true Mafia.

809
01:24:11.301 --> 01:24:14.346
The Archbishop and the Vatican Bank.
that's the big problem.

810
01:24:14.471 --> 01:24:18.225
They're the same problem.
B.J.. they're connected.

811
01:24:19.393 --> 01:24:22.229
The Archbishop has powerful friends.

812
01:24:24.523 --> 01:24:25.983
They totally protect him.

813
01:24:26.275 --> 01:24:30.529
Is there someone in the
Church we can turn to?

814
01:24:30.696 --> 01:24:34.032
Someone we can tell
our problem to?

815
01:24:35.409 --> 01:24:37.286
Cardinal Lamberto.

816
01:24:37.494 --> 01:24:42.541
A wise and good man...
very influential.

817
01:24:43.041 --> 01:24:46.044
He will see you.

818
01:24:50.924 --> 01:24:56.221
I will see this Cardinal Lamberto
and see if we can work things out.

819
01:24:58.056 --> 01:25:02.227
You honour your agreements.
but you are dealing with crooks.

820
01:25:03.353 --> 01:25:05.230
They have no honour.

821
01:25:07.316 --> 01:25:08.859
My word is final.

822
01:25:19.620 --> 01:25:23.790
Politics and crime.
they're the same thing.

823
01:25:44.686 --> 01:25:50.984
I've invited you all here to celebrate
my son's debut in an opera house...

824
01:25:51.652 --> 01:25:53.278
We'll play "Philadelphia".

825
01:25:54.780 --> 01:25:58.826
Seven cards. Two down. four up.
Deuces and one-eyed jacks are wild.

826
01:25:58.951 --> 01:26:01.411
...in the opera "Cavallaria Rusticana".

827
01:26:01.537 --> 01:26:05.624
- It's "Cavalleria Rusticana." Dad.
- "Cavalleria."

828
01:26:05.749 --> 01:26:10.087
I think I have tickets to the wrong opera.
I've been in New York too long.

829
01:26:11.171 --> 01:26:12.756
You will all receive tickets.
so come on time.

830
01:26:12.798 --> 01:26:14.341
You will all receive tickets.
so come on time.

831
01:26:14.466 --> 01:26:16.677
Dad. I've got a present for you.

832
01:26:20.472 --> 01:26:24.351
It comes from the town of Corleone
and it's authentic Sicilian.

833
01:26:25.561 --> 01:26:28.480
And... I learnt it for you.

834
01:27:54.775 --> 01:27:59.696
<i>She was wonderful. beautiful.
I loved her. And then she died.</i>

835
01:28:01.281 --> 01:28:05.953
My trusted bodyguard
planted a bomb in my car.

836
01:28:07.663 --> 01:28:09.748
She drove it before I did.

837
01:28:11.250 --> 01:28:14.169
Why is such a beautiful country
so violent?

838
01:28:14.711 --> 01:28:16.213
History.

839
01:28:16.380 --> 01:28:20.551
Mom was telling me about when your
biggest worry was passing your exams.

840
01:28:20.843 --> 01:28:23.929
- Yes. it was then.
- I worry about you now.

841
01:28:24.555 --> 01:28:29.184
Oh. Mary. you're such a
warm-hearted girl. You always were.

842
01:28:29.768 --> 01:28:32.980
- I love my family.
- Even your cousin Vincent?

843
01:28:37.067 --> 01:28:38.861
I really love him.

844
01:28:40.320 --> 01:28:43.323
- He's your first cousin.
- Then I love him first.

845
01:28:44.408 --> 01:28:46.827
Mary. you can't see him.

846
01:28:47.661 --> 01:28:49.746
Just don't see him any more.

847
01:28:50.747 --> 01:28:53.750
He's right. It's too dangerous.

848
01:28:56.211 --> 01:28:59.047
Mary. you can't see him any more.

849
01:28:59.465 --> 01:29:01.550
- Not in that fashion.
- No.

850
01:29:03.260 --> 01:29:06.388
- Please. promise me.
- No!

851
01:29:06.513 --> 01:29:08.765
- Obey me on this.
- No. Dad!

852
01:29:13.979 --> 01:29:17.733
Mary is smart. Dad.
She'll understand eventually.

853
01:29:40.088 --> 01:29:42.549
<i>Bella cugina... Tesoro mio.</i>

854
01:29:53.727 --> 01:29:55.854
- You wanted to see me?
- Yeah.

855
01:29:56.855 --> 01:29:59.942
I want you to do something for me.
It's dangerous.

856
01:30:01.777 --> 01:30:04.780
Good. I'm in. What do you need?

857
01:30:05.656 --> 01:30:08.617
I want you to sell your soul
to Don Altobello.

858
01:30:09.368 --> 01:30:10.911
To betray me.

859
01:30:14.248 --> 01:30:16.083
He'd never believe me.

860
01:30:17.167 --> 01:30:19.378
- That depends.
- Sit down.

861
01:30:22.256 --> 01:30:23.674
I have an idea.

862
01:30:25.342 --> 01:30:28.595
See if you can learn
how high Altobello is connected.

863
01:30:32.724 --> 01:30:34.393
Arrange a meeting.

864
01:30:37.020 --> 01:30:41.191
You say how devoted you are to me.
Tell him your problems.

865
01:30:42.401 --> 01:30:44.987
- Ask for his help.
- What problems?

866
01:30:47.072 --> 01:30:49.783
That you want to run away
with my daughter.

867
01:30:50.534 --> 01:30:53.871
But you know that if you do.
I will become your enemy.

868
01:30:58.917 --> 01:31:02.087
- You know that I would never do that.
- I know.

869
01:31:03.422 --> 01:31:07.634
<i>Ask Altobello to speak to me.
To further the marriage.</i>

870
01:31:08.385 --> 01:31:12.848
But you're cousins. after all. Michael
was always a little old-fashioned.

871
01:31:14.224 --> 01:31:18.854
Say you can't belong to my legitimate
world. That you want your own family.

872
01:31:19.688 --> 01:31:22.816
I could straighten out
what Joey Zasa left behind.

873
01:31:24.359 --> 01:31:27.196
If you could use your friendship
to persuade him.

874
01:31:28.197 --> 01:31:30.949
I would be indebted to you forever.

875
01:31:32.868 --> 01:31:36.330
A Corleone knows the value
of such a friend.

876
01:31:38.123 --> 01:31:40.375
Then you would work for me?

877
01:31:41.293 --> 01:31:42.377
<i>S�.</i>

878
01:31:45.005 --> 01:31:47.508
<i>Bacio la mano. Don Altobello.</i>

879
01:31:50.511 --> 01:31:55.307
If he hints that he wants you
to betray me. get insulted.

880
01:31:55.933 --> 01:31:57.893
because that's his trap.

881
01:32:04.358 --> 01:32:07.361
You're not telling me
the whole truth. Vincenzo.

882
01:32:10.489 --> 01:32:15.869
Isn't it true. that with Michael gone.
the girl controls everything?

883
01:32:20.040 --> 01:32:23.502
- Leave the girl out of this.
- Of course. you love her.

884
01:32:23.627 --> 01:32:25.212
And she loves you.

885
01:32:45.149 --> 01:32:48.152
I guessed it. didn't I?

886
01:32:49.653 --> 01:32:54.241
You're a wise man. Don Altobello.
I'll be learning a lot from you.

887
01:32:55.284 --> 01:32:58.787
The richest man is the one
with the most powerful friends.

888
01:33:01.206 --> 01:33:03.834
It's my duty to make the introductions.

889
01:33:10.340 --> 01:33:12.301
Don Lucchesi.

890
01:33:14.887 --> 01:33:20.309
Don Altobello tells me that you have
a strong character. A man of respect.

891
01:33:20.434 --> 01:33:23.604
This is the hero who put
Joey Zasa in his grave.

892
01:33:24.146 --> 01:33:27.816
If we'd known of his existence.
we wouldn't have backed Joey.

893
01:33:28.233 --> 01:33:30.194
No one wants another Joe.

894
01:33:32.279 --> 01:33:34.281
Let me be your friend.

895
01:33:34.781 --> 01:33:38.702
- Even the strongest man needs friends.
- I'm flattered.

896
01:33:40.120 --> 01:33:44.416
You're a man of finance and politics.
Things I don't understand.

897
01:33:46.126 --> 01:33:49.880
You understand guns.
Finance is a gun.

898
01:33:51.048 --> 01:33:55.052
Politics is knowing
when to pull the trigger.

899
01:33:59.431 --> 01:34:00.933
How can I help?

900
01:34:01.725 --> 01:34:02.976
<i>Vieni?</i>

901
01:34:05.979 --> 01:34:10.984
Blessed is the peacemaker.
for he can be called the child of God.

902
01:34:11.401 --> 01:34:14.029
<i>- Tu parli Italiano un poco?
- S�.</i>

903
01:34:35.509 --> 01:34:38.178
The wheelchair. for Don Tommasino.

904
01:34:45.853 --> 01:34:50.440
I trusted this business arrangement
with the Archbishop. I trusted him.

905
01:34:50.566 --> 01:34:53.527
I was sure his honesty
was beyond a doubt.

906
01:34:54.528 --> 01:34:58.532
But. as you see.
I'm now the victim of a swindle.

907
01:34:59.533 --> 01:35:04.830
He's stalling me. Vast monies have
gone to people in high political places

908
01:35:05.205 --> 01:35:08.041
and the Vatican Bank is the guarantor.

909
01:35:08.167 --> 01:35:13.088
If what you say is true.
there will be a great scandal.

910
01:35:15.215 --> 01:35:19.970
Look at this stone. It has been
in the water for a very long time.

911
01:35:20.137 --> 01:35:23.682
but the water has not penetrated it.

912
01:35:27.769 --> 01:35:28.937
Look...

913
01:35:30.022 --> 01:35:34.902
Perfectly dry. The same thing
has happened to men in Europe.

914
01:35:35.027 --> 01:35:38.947
For centuries they have been
surrounded by Christianity.

915
01:35:39.781 --> 01:35:45.412
but Christ has not penetrated.
Christ doesn't live within them.

916
01:35:49.374 --> 01:35:53.337
- What's happening?
- Could you get me something sweet?

917
01:35:53.462 --> 01:35:56.632
Some orange juice. candy...

918
01:36:00.260 --> 01:36:02.387
I have trouble with diabetes.

919
01:36:06.016 --> 01:36:08.185
My blood sugar goes low.

920
01:36:08.310 --> 01:36:09.978
I understand.

921
01:36:32.376 --> 01:36:35.087
It happens sometimes
when I'm under stress.

922
01:36:36.004 --> 01:36:37.464
I understand.

923
01:36:39.550 --> 01:36:43.095
To come to you
on such a delicate matter...

924
01:36:45.889 --> 01:36:50.185
Accusations against your Archbishop.
It was difficult for me.

925
01:36:51.937 --> 01:36:53.564
The mind suffers

926
01:36:54.064 --> 01:36:56.733
and the body cries out.

927
01:37:02.656 --> 01:37:04.074
That's true.

928
01:37:05.701 --> 01:37:09.329
Would you like to make
your confession?

929
01:37:15.836 --> 01:37:17.588
Your Eminence. I'm...

930
01:37:21.800 --> 01:37:26.930
It's been so long. I wouldn't...
I wouldn't know where to...

931
01:37:28.474 --> 01:37:30.225
It's been 30 years.

932
01:37:32.060 --> 01:37:34.605
I'd use up too much of your time. I think.

933
01:37:35.564 --> 01:37:37.983
I always have time to save souls.

934
01:37:39.568 --> 01:37:43.947
- Well. I'm beyond redemption.
- No. no...

935
01:37:52.998 --> 01:37:56.502
I hear the confessions
of my own priests here.

936
01:37:57.836 --> 01:38:01.215
Sometimes the desire to confess
is overwhelming.

937
01:38:01.924 --> 01:38:04.134
and we must seize the moment.

938
01:38:08.680 --> 01:38:12.142
What is the point of confessing
if I don't repent?

939
01:38:14.645 --> 01:38:16.897
I hear you are a practical man.

940
01:38:17.856 --> 01:38:19.817
What have you got to lose?

941
01:38:31.245 --> 01:38:32.496
Go on.

942
01:38:39.044 --> 01:38:40.129
I...

943
01:38:41.505 --> 01:38:43.257
...betrayed my wife.

944
01:38:45.008 --> 01:38:46.426
Go on. my son.

945
01:38:51.932 --> 01:38:53.600
I betrayed myself.

946
01:38:56.562 --> 01:38:57.980
I killed men.

947
01:39:01.942 --> 01:39:04.236
And I ordered men to be killed.

948
01:39:05.779 --> 01:39:07.698
Go on. my son. Go on.

949
01:39:13.620 --> 01:39:15.080
It's useless.

950
01:39:16.665 --> 01:39:18.250
Go on. my son.

951
01:39:19.626 --> 01:39:21.003
I killed...

952
01:39:25.966 --> 01:39:28.302
I ordered the death of my brother.

953
01:39:29.470 --> 01:39:31.138
He injured me.

954
01:39:32.723 --> 01:39:34.683
I killed my mother's son.

955
01:39:36.477 --> 01:39:38.395
I killed my father's son.

956
01:39:48.780 --> 01:39:52.951
Your sins are terrible.
and it is just that you suffer.

957
01:39:54.536 --> 01:39:56.788
Your life could be redeemed.

958
01:39:58.165 --> 01:40:01.794
but I know that you don't believe that.
You will not change.

959
01:40:31.240 --> 01:40:35.994
<i>Pope Paul VI. Supreme Pontiff
of the Roman Catholic Church...</i>

960
01:40:36.328 --> 01:40:39.373
<i>died last night at 9:40 p.m.</i>

961
01:40:39.957 --> 01:40:43.043
<i>The Pope was 81 years old...</i>

962
01:40:44.002 --> 01:40:47.339
<i>and had been in poor health
for the last several months.</i>

963
01:40:51.969 --> 01:40:53.220
Connie...

964
01:40:55.055 --> 01:40:59.184
All my life I've kept trying
to go up in society.

965
01:40:59.893 --> 01:41:02.646
To where everything higher up
was legal. straight...

966
01:41:04.690 --> 01:41:07.985
But the higher I go.
the more crooked it becomes.

967
01:41:10.696 --> 01:41:12.698
Where the hell does it end?

968
01:41:21.456 --> 01:41:24.668
They've been killing each other
for centuries here.

969
01:41:26.128 --> 01:41:29.965
For money. for pride. for family.

970
01:41:33.093 --> 01:41:36.889
<i>To keep from becoming the slaves
of the rich pezzi da novanta.</i>

971
01:41:43.729 --> 01:41:45.856
I made confession. Connie.

972
01:41:46.857 --> 01:41:48.775
I confessed my sins.

973
01:41:50.444 --> 01:41:55.240
Why? That's not like you. You don't
have to confess your sins to a stranger.

974
01:41:56.200 --> 01:41:57.618
It was the man.

975
01:41:58.660 --> 01:42:02.206
He's a good man. A true priest.

976
01:42:06.251 --> 01:42:08.170
He can change things.

977
01:42:10.380 --> 01:42:12.007
Michael...

978
01:42:13.425 --> 01:42:17.095
You know.
sometimes I think of poor Fredo.

979
01:42:17.971 --> 01:42:21.058
Drowned. It was God's will.

980
01:42:23.560 --> 01:42:25.646
It was a terrible accident.

981
01:42:27.064 --> 01:42:28.857
But it's finished.

982
01:42:33.779 --> 01:42:35.489
Michael. I love you.

983
01:42:37.783 --> 01:42:39.618
I'll always help you.

984
01:42:51.421 --> 01:42:52.881
Oh. Connie...

985
01:43:21.660 --> 01:43:28.333
I am honoured. Don Altobello. that
you've come from Palermo to visit me.

986
01:43:31.545 --> 01:43:36.300
Hey. the little kid! He's grown.

987
01:43:36.925 --> 01:43:38.635
Do the donkey for me.

988
01:43:55.569 --> 01:43:59.406
It's been some time since we
did business together.

989
01:44:03.243 --> 01:44:07.998
You are my "ace in the hole."
as we say in America.

990
01:44:08.123 --> 01:44:13.712
I have a stone in my shoe.
You can remove it.

991
01:44:20.719 --> 01:44:23.472
Only one stone?

992
01:44:25.474 --> 01:44:31.104
It's dangerous. A famous man.

993
01:44:31.396 --> 01:44:34.691
You will have to take precautions.

994
01:44:37.486 --> 01:44:42.699
Tell me what to do.
Then I will tell you my price.

995
01:44:46.745 --> 01:44:49.414
Ah. what bread!

996
01:44:53.335 --> 01:44:57.297
Olive oil...

997
01:45:00.342 --> 01:45:03.679
Virgin... only in Sicily.

998
01:45:06.098 --> 01:45:07.224
<i>Alla salute!</i>

999
01:45:07.349 --> 01:45:10.060
To death.

1000
01:45:23.073 --> 01:45:24.575
Kay!

1001
01:45:24.700 --> 01:45:26.869
- Connie!
- How are you?

1002
01:45:26.994 --> 01:45:29.913
Mary. I've missed you.

1003
01:45:30.455 --> 01:45:33.959
- Hello. Michael.
- Mom. look at this.

1004
01:45:37.921 --> 01:45:43.552
- It's too bad Douglas couldn't come.
- I know. He had a very important trial.

1005
01:45:43.677 --> 01:45:45.554
I know he wanted to come.

1006
01:45:46.722 --> 01:45:48.640
- The car is...
- Okay.

1007
01:45:50.559 --> 01:45:56.440
- Well. your son is an artist.
- Oh. yes. Thanks to you.

1008
01:45:57.107 --> 01:46:01.236
- What for?
- For making me let him go.

1009
01:46:01.945 --> 01:46:06.783
Well. after all these years.
here I am in Sicily for the first time.

1010
01:46:06.909 --> 01:46:09.870
- I want to get a picture of you together.
- Okay.

1011
01:46:11.788 --> 01:46:13.457
Hey. Dad. Smile!

1012
01:46:17.795 --> 01:46:20.506
I see you still have Al Neri. Why?

1013
01:46:21.757 --> 01:46:25.177
I need him. He helps me
get in and out of the car.

1014
01:46:26.345 --> 01:46:29.890
- He carries my briefcase.
- You're still a liar. Michael.

1015
01:46:31.141 --> 01:46:36.104
Let me show you Sicily. the real Sicily.
So you'll understand the family history.

1016
01:46:37.231 --> 01:46:39.900
I think I understand
it well enough.

1017
01:47:29.491 --> 01:47:35.164
Anthony. I have something you made
for me a very long time ago.

1018
01:47:36.832 --> 01:47:39.460
- Might bring you luck.
- Thanks.

1019
01:47:43.547 --> 01:47:46.633
You saved it... I remember.

1020
01:47:50.512 --> 01:47:51.972
Thank you. Dad.

1021
01:47:53.557 --> 01:47:55.184
I'm proud of you.

1022
01:47:55.976 --> 01:47:57.394
Thank you.

1023
01:48:13.076 --> 01:48:15.704
- Are they as good as they look?
- Better.

1024
01:48:15.829 --> 01:48:20.042
They're the best. As long as they are
around. Uncle Michael is safe.

1025
01:48:20.709 --> 01:48:22.211
Goodbye.

1026
01:48:24.755 --> 01:48:27.800
- Tell your father I'll be back for dinner.
- Okay.

1027
01:48:28.300 --> 01:48:30.803
- Have fun.
- Tell Tony to wait for me.

1028
01:48:30.928 --> 01:48:32.262
I will.

1029
01:48:34.723 --> 01:48:38.101
<i>Buongiorno. signora. At your service.</i>

1030
01:48:41.980 --> 01:48:44.691
If I see Dad. I'll tell him you left.

1031
01:48:49.988 --> 01:48:53.450
You're the only one left
with my father's strength.

1032
01:48:55.661 --> 01:48:59.373
If anything happens to Michael.
I want you to strike back.

1033
01:49:02.251 --> 01:49:04.294
I'll have everything ready.

1034
01:49:07.631 --> 01:49:09.216
Do you swear?

1035
01:49:16.306 --> 01:49:17.808
I swear to you.

1036
01:49:46.962 --> 01:49:48.505
Here it is.

1037
01:49:50.299 --> 01:49:52.759
The house where my father was born.

1038
01:49:53.844 --> 01:49:58.974
This is where they came to take him
when he was a boy. To kill him.

1039
01:50:02.060 --> 01:50:03.729
Wait...

1040
01:50:04.480 --> 01:50:06.273
Listen to that.

1041
01:50:24.708 --> 01:50:26.585
You know Mary's in love.

1042
01:50:28.086 --> 01:50:29.588
Yes. I know.

1043
01:50:30.798 --> 01:50:34.426
With a handsome young Italian man
with dark eyes...

1044
01:50:35.886 --> 01:50:37.596
I won't allow it.

1045
01:50:40.307 --> 01:50:43.769
It's wrong.
It's wrong and it's dangerous.

1046
01:50:44.019 --> 01:50:46.814
"Oh father. my father!"

1047
01:50:47.523 --> 01:50:49.733
"Give me some time to pray
to the Lord."

1048
01:50:50.859 --> 01:50:53.779
The Baroness of Carini had
betrayed her husband...

1049
01:50:54.404 --> 01:50:57.032
and fallen in love with her cousin.

1050
01:50:57.449 --> 01:50:59.368
"There will be no forgiveness!"

1051
01:50:59.660 --> 01:51:03.080
Her father stabbed her through
the heart.

1052
01:51:14.883 --> 01:51:16.260
Honour. huh?

1053
01:51:35.154 --> 01:51:38.031
I remember the time you came
to my parents' house

1054
01:51:38.157 --> 01:51:41.535
and told me about the family business.

1055
01:51:41.660 --> 01:51:46.373
How you'd never have anything
to do with it. You sounded like Tony.

1056
01:51:47.499 --> 01:51:49.376
I was a lot like Tony.

1057
01:51:56.675 --> 01:51:59.386
- I can barely see him... Kay?
- What?

1058
01:51:59.511 --> 01:52:02.014
- Do you mind driving?
- What's wrong?

1059
01:52:02.181 --> 01:52:04.975
My eyes.
Sometimes they're all right. but...

1060
01:52:06.685 --> 01:52:08.896
I have to see Don Tommasino...

1061
01:52:12.441 --> 01:52:13.775
Well...

1062
01:52:14.985 --> 01:52:18.155
- There are no bodyguards today.
- I really snuck away.

1063
01:52:25.078 --> 01:52:29.291
Father. where are you going?
Would you like a ride?

1064
01:52:38.091 --> 01:52:42.137
I know you. You're Mosca
of Montelepre.

1065
01:52:43.222 --> 01:52:46.850
You were an assassin then
and you're an assassin now.

1066
01:52:47.142 --> 01:52:50.312
I know Michael Corleone
is at your house.

1067
01:52:50.729 --> 01:52:52.856
I will pass through the gates
with you.

1068
01:53:09.081 --> 01:53:10.749
How are you?

1069
01:53:10.874 --> 01:53:14.253
This is Calo. one of my bodyguards
in the old days.

1070
01:53:19.883 --> 01:53:22.344
- We can wait here.
- You want a drink?

1071
01:53:27.599 --> 01:53:30.310
I spent a lot of time in this room...

1072
01:53:31.395 --> 01:53:33.313
...thinking of you.

1073
01:53:36.233 --> 01:53:38.277
And then you got married.

1074
01:53:41.780 --> 01:53:44.992
- I still thought of you.
- What's in that room?

1075
01:53:49.621 --> 01:53:53.000
This is dangerous for you. This is Sicily.

1076
01:53:56.044 --> 01:53:58.255
- I love this country.
- Why?

1077
01:54:00.757 --> 01:54:06.388
Well. all through history. terrible things
have happened to these people.

1078
01:54:07.389 --> 01:54:09.516
Terrible injustices.

1079
01:54:10.392 --> 01:54:15.022
But they still expect good.
rather than bad. will happen to them.

1080
01:54:15.606 --> 01:54:17.774
Sort of like me and you?

1081
01:54:21.570 --> 01:54:24.072
- How so?
- I'm still here. right?

1082
01:54:25.032 --> 01:54:27.951
We do have a bad history.
but I'm still here.

1083
01:54:28.076 --> 01:54:30.621
Yes. you are. but with dread.

1084
01:54:35.417 --> 01:54:37.044
Give me the order!

1085
01:54:37.503 --> 01:54:40.464
Is that supposed to make me
not dread you?

1086
01:54:42.633 --> 01:54:44.760
We're in Sicily. It's opera.

1087
01:54:47.262 --> 01:54:48.639
Okay.

1088
01:54:51.183 --> 01:54:52.851
What do we do now?

1089
01:54:55.521 --> 01:54:59.191
Be reasonable.
Let's try not to hurt each other.

1090
01:55:06.740 --> 01:55:08.659
I want you to forgive me.

1091
01:55:11.411 --> 01:55:14.206
- For what?
- Everything.

1092
01:55:17.793 --> 01:55:19.795
Oh. like God?

1093
01:55:21.630 --> 01:55:24.091
No. I need something a little closer.

1094
01:55:26.927 --> 01:55:29.930
You couldn't understand.
back in those days.

1095
01:55:31.390 --> 01:55:36.019
I loved my father. I swore I would
never be a man like him.

1096
01:55:36.145 --> 01:55:39.773
but I loved him and he was in danger.
What could I do?

1097
01:55:40.440 --> 01:55:43.026
And then later. you were in danger.

1098
01:55:43.902 --> 01:55:47.072
Our children were in danger.
What could I do?

1099
01:55:48.115 --> 01:55:53.120
You were all that I... loved and valued
most in the world.

1100
01:55:55.497 --> 01:55:57.916
Now I'm losing you. I lost you.

1101
01:55:58.667 --> 01:56:00.419
You're gone.

1102
01:56:01.628 --> 01:56:04.298
And it was all for nothing. So...

1103
01:56:08.844 --> 01:56:13.599
You have to understand.
I had a whole different destiny planned.

1104
01:56:17.102 --> 01:56:18.854
All right. I'll stop.

1105
01:56:28.989 --> 01:56:32.743
I really don't know what you
want from me. Michael.

1106
01:56:33.243 --> 01:56:37.206
- I mean...
- I'm not the man that you think I am.

1107
01:56:38.957 --> 01:56:42.085
- I don't know.
- I love you. Kay.

1108
01:56:44.129 --> 01:56:45.923
Don't dread me any more.

1109
01:56:51.512 --> 01:56:55.182
You know. every night here in Sicily...

1110
01:56:57.309 --> 01:57:02.064
...I dream about my wife
and my children...

1111
01:57:05.484 --> 01:57:07.319
...and how I lost them.

1112
01:57:09.488 --> 01:57:14.910
I guess that if it's any consolation.
I want you to know that...

1113
01:57:18.288 --> 01:57:19.623
...that...

1114
01:57:20.666 --> 01:57:22.876
...I always loved you. Michael.

1115
01:57:24.378 --> 01:57:26.004
And you know...

1116
01:57:27.798 --> 01:57:30.050
...always. I always will.

1117
01:57:57.494 --> 01:57:59.663
What is it? What's wrong?

1118
01:57:59.955 --> 01:58:02.583
They found Don Tommasino shot.

1119
01:58:03.876 --> 01:58:06.003
Is he dead?

1120
01:58:07.713 --> 01:58:11.049
My master is dead.
Blood calls for blood.

1121
01:58:11.717 --> 01:58:14.386
I must have revenge!

1122
01:58:18.098 --> 01:58:23.020
Some day. you may have to do
a difficult service for me.

1123
01:58:23.270 --> 01:58:24.771
Command me.

1124
01:58:26.607 --> 01:58:27.649
It never ends.

1125
01:58:27.816 --> 01:58:29.818
I will avenge him!

1126
01:58:44.458 --> 01:58:45.793
Totals...

1127
01:58:47.753 --> 01:58:50.005
Lorscheider. 1 vote.

1128
01:58:50.672 --> 01:58:53.550
Siri. 11 votes.

1129
01:58:54.259 --> 01:58:57.179
Lamberto. 99 votes.

1130
01:59:02.476 --> 01:59:07.523
Do you accept your election
as supreme pontiff?

1131
01:59:08.148 --> 01:59:13.695
Oh God. shed light on the decision
they have taken on my behalf.

1132
01:59:14.571 --> 01:59:16.114
I accept.

1133
01:59:16.323 --> 01:59:18.826
By what name do you
wish to be called?

1134
01:59:19.159 --> 01:59:21.995
John Paul the First.

1135
01:59:50.482 --> 01:59:55.112
I will do things "right away."
rather than in "a little while"...

1136
01:59:57.156 --> 02:00:02.244
<i>Frederick Keinszig. known as "God's
Banker". has been reported missing.</i>

1137
02:00:02.369 --> 02:00:09.376
<i>He was last seen leaving the Rome
offices of Vatican owned Immobiliare.</i>

1138
02:00:09.626 --> 02:00:12.921
<i>Also missing was a large sum
of money and several documents.</i>

1139
02:00:14.381 --> 02:00:16.300
Keinszig. you fool.

1140
02:00:19.761 --> 02:00:24.433
<i>His absence casts further suspicion
on the dealings of the Vatican Bank.</i>

1141
02:00:24.558 --> 02:00:27.102
<i>For several years.
the bank and its companies</i>

1142
02:00:27.227 --> 02:00:31.273
<i>have been the object of allegations
of disreputable business practises.</i>

1143
02:00:32.483 --> 02:00:36.403
Lucchesi. will you please
try to understand?

1144
02:00:37.821 --> 02:00:41.867
I have phoned him.
I have waited here by the phone.

1145
02:00:44.453 --> 02:00:47.790
<i>You would do well to remember.
Mr Lucchesi.</i>

1146
02:00:48.624 --> 02:00:55.005
that this Pope has very different ideas
from the last one.

1147
02:01:16.360 --> 02:01:18.278
Goodbye. my old friend.

1148
02:01:20.906 --> 02:01:23.492
You could have lived a little longer.

1149
02:01:24.409 --> 02:01:26.745
I could be closer to my dream.

1150
02:01:32.876 --> 02:01:35.254
You were so loved. Don Tommasino.

1151
02:01:39.967 --> 02:01:43.470
Why was I so feared. and you so loved?

1152
02:01:44.680 --> 02:01:46.181
What was it?

1153
02:01:47.349 --> 02:01:49.434
I was no less honourable.

1154
02:01:51.520 --> 02:01:53.230
I wanted to do good.

1155
02:01:57.234 --> 02:01:59.987
What betrayed me? My mind? My heart?

1156
02:02:02.990 --> 02:02:05.284
Why do I condemn myself so?

1157
02:02:11.623 --> 02:02:13.250
I swear.

1158
02:02:13.709 --> 02:02:15.836
on the lives of my children...

1159
02:02:20.257 --> 02:02:22.759
Give me a chance to redeem myself...

1160
02:02:26.597 --> 02:02:30.017
...and I will sin no more.

1161
02:02:53.332 --> 02:02:57.044
You look pale. Bad news?
Tell me right away.

1162
02:02:59.129 --> 02:03:01.423
It's not just a bad banking deal.

1163
02:03:02.466 --> 02:03:04.426
These guys are butchers.

1164
02:03:05.636 --> 02:03:08.138
- What guys?
- Lucchesi.

1165
02:03:09.973 --> 02:03:13.685
He controls all of them:
Altobello. the Archbishop...

1166
02:03:15.437 --> 02:03:17.940
...others higher up. P2 maybe.

1167
02:03:18.065 --> 02:03:20.943
Secret unknown. They're running things.

1168
02:03:24.655 --> 02:03:29.159
- I'm in their way.
- He's hired an assassin to kill you.

1169
02:03:29.785 --> 02:03:32.287
A Sicilian. I don't know his name.

1170
02:03:34.414 --> 02:03:36.416
But they say he never fails.

1171
02:03:37.668 --> 02:03:39.670
Then no one is safe.

1172
02:03:42.422 --> 02:03:44.675
Even the new Pope is in danger.

1173
02:03:45.759 --> 02:03:48.679
We still have time. We can prevent this.

1174
02:03:53.934 --> 02:03:56.103
I tried. Vincent.

1175
02:03:58.230 --> 02:03:59.648
I tried...

1176
02:04:00.941 --> 02:04:05.154
...to keep everything from coming
to this. But it's not possible.

1177
02:04:06.697 --> 02:04:08.323
Not in this world.

1178
02:04:09.908 --> 02:04:11.493
Give me the order.

1179
02:04:15.289 --> 02:04:17.458
You won't be able to go back.

1180
02:04:18.500 --> 02:04:20.461
- You'll be like me.
- Good.

1181
02:04:22.254 --> 02:04:24.131
All my life I wanted out.

1182
02:04:24.840 --> 02:04:26.758
I wanted the family out.

1183
02:04:28.844 --> 02:04:30.554
I don't want out.

1184
02:04:31.054 --> 02:04:33.682
I want the power to preserve the family.

1185
02:04:38.228 --> 02:04:40.314
I'm asking for the order.

1186
02:05:00.501 --> 02:05:02.002
It's done.

1187
02:05:03.420 --> 02:05:05.589
Because I can't do it any more.

1188
02:05:09.760 --> 02:05:13.138
Well. it doesn't matter.
Vincent knows what to do.

1189
02:05:13.263 --> 02:05:17.976
Come on outside.
Take a rest and don't think about it.

1190
02:05:18.393 --> 02:05:21.146
- All I do is think about it.
- I'm your son.

1191
02:05:22.314 --> 02:05:24.316
Command me in all things.

1192
02:05:26.610 --> 02:05:28.403
Give up my daughter.

1193
02:05:31.365 --> 02:05:33.408
That's the price you pay...

1194
02:05:34.535 --> 02:05:36.537
...for the life you choose.

1195
02:06:01.728 --> 02:06:03.147
Nephew...

1196
02:06:05.566 --> 02:06:07.484
...from this moment on...

1197
02:06:08.861 --> 02:06:11.238
...call yourself Vincent Corleone.

1198
02:06:15.868 --> 02:06:17.035
Sit.

1199
02:06:31.633 --> 02:06:33.135
Don Vincenzo...

1200
02:06:38.974 --> 02:06:40.559
Don Corleone...

1201
02:06:43.979 --> 02:06:45.939
Don Vincenzo Corleone...

1202
02:08:15.946 --> 02:08:18.157
<i>E tu. Vincenzo...</i>

1203
02:08:18.282 --> 02:08:22.661
I know how you feel about Michael.
but you can't save him.

1204
02:08:23.620 --> 02:08:24.872
He's lost.

1205
02:08:26.540 --> 02:08:28.292
Think of yourself.

1206
02:08:29.251 --> 02:08:31.837
What's your answer. Vincent?

1207
02:08:33.338 --> 02:08:34.965
Enjoy the opera.

1208
02:08:37.009 --> 02:08:38.927
It's all taken care of.

1209
02:08:44.308 --> 02:08:46.977
Check the bar. I'll check the top floor.

1210
02:08:50.689 --> 02:08:54.818
"Here's hoping Tony sings better at the
Teatro Massimo than in the shower.

1211
02:08:54.943 --> 02:08:57.070
"Love. Douglas."

1212
02:08:57.196 --> 02:09:00.449
- My darling Constanza!
- Don Altobello.

1213
02:09:01.366 --> 02:09:04.244
- This is a great occasion.
- Come. sit down.

1214
02:09:08.749 --> 02:09:13.003
Happy birthday.
You're 80. but don't look more than 60.

1215
02:09:13.128 --> 02:09:14.296
You're the only one who remembered.

1216
02:09:14.296 --> 02:09:15.422
You're the only one who remembered.

1217
02:09:15.547 --> 02:09:17.132
We�ve just got the word.

1218
02:09:17.299 --> 02:09:20.511
The Pope has ratified
the Immobiliare deal. We've won.

1219
02:09:20.636 --> 02:09:22.179
Congratulations.

1220
02:09:24.973 --> 02:09:27.100
Strange how things work.

1221
02:09:27.226 --> 02:09:31.063
The Pope is doing what you
said he'd do. He's cleaning house.

1222
02:09:32.147 --> 02:09:35.776
He should be careful.
It's dangerous to be an honest man.

1223
02:09:41.782 --> 02:09:44.701
I want to put more muscle backstage
with Tony.

1224
02:09:56.338 --> 02:09:59.424
On your birthday you used to
shower me with treats.

1225
02:09:59.550 --> 02:10:01.260
Tootsie Rolls!

1226
02:10:02.177 --> 02:10:07.349
The nuns who made this cannoli took a
vow of silence. They're the very finest.

1227
02:10:11.061 --> 02:10:13.689
- Hey.
- Hey. cous.

1228
02:10:15.691 --> 02:10:18.318
Hi. Where's your leather?

1229
02:10:22.364 --> 02:10:23.740
Stop it.

1230
02:10:29.580 --> 02:10:32.541
You're so thin. You eat it.

1231
02:10:48.599 --> 02:10:49.808
<i>� buono.</i>

1232
02:10:50.350 --> 02:10:52.561
<i>Grazie!</i>

1233
02:10:55.397 --> 02:10:59.485
It's over. There are things I have to do
that you can't be part of.

1234
02:10:59.610 --> 02:11:02.362
It's not your father's decision. it's mine.

1235
02:11:04.239 --> 02:11:06.200
Don't hate your father.

1236
02:11:08.410 --> 02:11:12.039
There are things I'll be part of
that you can't be around.

1237
02:11:13.749 --> 02:11:16.335
After tonight.
you won't see me any more.

1238
02:11:20.589 --> 02:11:24.051
You've got to understand. Mary.
You've got to understand.

1239
02:11:25.093 --> 02:11:26.595
I'll always love you.

1240
02:11:39.316 --> 02:11:41.026
Love somebody else.

1241
02:15:13.197 --> 02:15:16.950
- They won't try anything.
- Everything's fine. It's all clear.

1242
02:15:17.075 --> 02:15:19.745
I've already sent Al Neri to the Vatican.

1243
02:15:31.757 --> 02:15:34.134
Mr Lucchesi's house?

1244
02:15:34.259 --> 02:15:35.260
Yes.

1245
02:15:35.719 --> 02:15:39.723
I bring a message from
Michael Corleone.

1246
02:15:41.099 --> 02:15:42.392
Let him in.

1247
02:17:07.936 --> 02:17:09.730
<i>Buona sera.</i>

1248
02:20:22.589 --> 02:20:24.299
Good. You got him.

1249
02:21:14.475 --> 02:21:17.769
<i>Tonight the Corleone family
settles its accounts.</i>

1250
02:21:18.103 --> 02:21:22.399
<i>Keinszig...
That little Swiss banker fuck.</i>

1251
02:21:23.692 --> 02:21:27.237
<i>He's been swindling everyone
from the beginning. Fuck him.</i>

1252
02:21:28.989 --> 02:21:31.533
<i>Don Lucchesi. my friend.</i>

1253
02:21:31.658 --> 02:21:34.119
<i>Calo will pay him a visit at his home.</i>

1254
02:21:36.705 --> 02:21:40.000
<i>Neri. take a train to Rome.</i>

1255
02:21:41.418 --> 02:21:43.837
<i>Light a candle for the Archbishop.</i>

1256
02:22:16.912 --> 02:22:20.207
Tea. Your Holiness? It will help
you sleep.

1257
02:22:42.980 --> 02:22:45.774
This is from Vincent Corleone.

1258
02:23:41.622 --> 02:23:46.376
It's serious. Our man inside the Vatican
says there's a plot against the Pope.

1259
02:23:46.502 --> 02:23:48.545
He'll have a heart attack?

1260
02:23:55.469 --> 02:24:00.432
This Pope has powerful enemies.
We may not be in time to save him.

1261
02:24:03.310 --> 02:24:04.812
Let's go back.

1262
02:24:38.011 --> 02:24:39.513
<i>Eminenza...</i>

1263
02:24:54.653 --> 02:24:57.156
The Holy Father is dead!

1264
02:26:23.784 --> 02:26:25.160
Sleep.

1265
02:26:25.953 --> 02:26:27.579
Sleep. Godfather.

1266
02:26:42.678 --> 02:26:44.096
Our friend's dead.

1267
02:27:34.980 --> 02:27:36.899
Speak... tell me.

1268
02:27:38.317 --> 02:27:44.448
You have lost the
faith of the people.

1269
02:27:45.741 --> 02:27:49.995
He who builds on the people
builds on mud.

1270
02:27:50.412 --> 02:27:54.041
And Michael Corleone's message?

1271
02:28:10.140 --> 02:28:16.313
It's very important.
I must whisper it in your ear.

1272
02:28:20.025 --> 02:28:21.902
He's clean.

1273
02:28:39.670 --> 02:28:42.256
Power wears out those
who don't have it.

1274
02:30:07.424 --> 02:30:10.594
- I like this outfit.
- I figured you would.

1275
02:30:10.719 --> 02:30:12.304
Say hello.

1276
02:30:33.450 --> 02:30:37.162
- Can I talk to you now?
- No. it's not a good time.

1277
02:30:37.287 --> 02:30:40.833
- You�re just like my father.
- Stay with the family. Go on.

1278
02:30:42.501 --> 02:30:44.253
- Talk to me.
- The twins are dead.

1279
02:30:44.419 --> 02:30:48.298
In about one minute. there will be
carabinieri all over this place.

1280
02:30:49.216 --> 02:30:51.969
Get everybody to the cars. quietly.

1281
02:30:52.094 --> 02:30:53.595
- Got it.
- Quiet.

1282
02:31:07.734 --> 02:31:11.113
The name Corleone
will be associated with a voice.

1283
02:31:20.205 --> 02:31:21.415
Dad...

1284
02:31:40.267 --> 02:31:43.979
Dad... Why are you doing this to me?

1285
02:31:52.780 --> 02:31:55.199
Move back. move back.

1286
02:31:56.575 --> 02:32:00.454
- You don't have to do this to me.
- Do what? What do you mean?

1287
02:32:25.854 --> 02:32:27.022
Dad...

1288
02:32:43.413 --> 02:32:45.290
No! Mary!

1289
02:32:48.460 --> 02:32:49.753
God. no!

1290
